1
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:49,634
Did you hear that?

2
00:02:49,659 --> 00:02:52,860
They shut down the main reactor.
We'll be destroyed for sure.

3
00:02:53,027 --> 00:02:54,827
This is madness.

4
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:06,517
We're doomed.

5
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:11,100
There'll be no escape
for the princess this time.

6
00:03:13,626 --> 00:03:15,726
What's that?

7
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,000
R2-D2, where are you?

8
00:05:16,468 --> 00:05:18,671
At last! Where have you been?

9
00:05:18,993 --> 00:05:21,895
They're heading in this direction.
What are we going to do?

10
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:26,421
We'll be sent to the spice mines of Kessel,
or smashed into who knows what!

11
00:05:26,945 --> 00:05:29,445
Wait a minute.
Where are you going?

12
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:44,700
The Death Star plans are not
in the main computer.

13
00:05:45,052 --> 00:05:47,788
Where are those transmissions
you intercepted?

14
00:05:47,813 --> 00:05:50,485
What have you done with those plans?

15
00:05:50,509 --> 00:05:53,019
We intercepted no transmissions.

16
00:05:53,119 --> 00:05:55,163
This is a consular ship.

17
00:05:55,369 --> 00:05:57,189
We're on a diplomatic mission.

18
00:05:57,289 --> 00:06:01,789
If this is a consular ship,
where is the ambassador?

19
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:09,005
Commander, tear this ship apart
until you've found those plans,

20
00:06:09,030 --> 00:06:12,030
and bring me the passengers!
I want them alive!

21
00:06:24,477 --> 00:06:26,477
There's one. Set for stun.

22
00:06:31,857 --> 00:06:35,000
She'll be all right.
Inform Lord Vader we have a prisoner.

23
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:39,533
Hey! You're not permitted in there.
It's restricted.

24
00:06:39,695 --> 00:06:41,877
You'll be deactivated for sure.

25
00:06:43,383 --> 00:06:46,231
Don't you call me a mindless philosopher,
you overweight glob of grease!

26
00:06:46,256 --> 00:06:48,356
Now come out before somebody sees you.

27
00:06:50,122 --> 00:06:53,557
Secret mission? What plans?
What are you talking about?

28
00:06:53,581 --> 00:06:55,677
I'm not getting in there.

29
00:06:58,383 --> 00:07:00,383
I'm going to regret this.

30
00:07:07,685 --> 00:07:08,673
There goes another one.

31
00:07:08,698 --> 00:07:11,241
Hold your fire.
There's no life forms.

32
00:07:11,265 --> 00:07:12,630
It must have short-circuited.

33
00:07:12,771 --> 00:07:16,065
That's funny. The damage
doesn't look as bad from out here.

34
00:07:18,186 --> 00:07:20,386
Are you sure this thing is safe?

35
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:22,507
Oh.

36
00:07:39,224 --> 00:07:41,825
Darth Vader.
Only you could be so bold.

37
00:07:41,925 --> 00:07:44,253
The Imperial Senate will not
sit still for this.

38
00:07:44,277 --> 00:07:45,553
When they hear you've
attacked a diplomatic—

39
00:07:45,578 --> 00:07:47,660
Don't act so surprised, Your Highness.

40
00:07:47,684 --> 00:07:49,666
You weren't on any mercy mission this time.

41
00:07:50,042 --> 00:07:53,815
Several transmissions were
beamed to this ship by rebel spies.

42
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,709
I want to know what happened
to the plans they sent you.

43
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,903
I don't know what you're talking about.

44
00:07:58,928 --> 00:08:02,499
I'm a member of the Imperial Senate
on a diplomatic mission to Alderaan.

45
00:08:02,605 --> 00:08:05,365
You are part of the Rebel Alliance
and a traitor.

46
00:08:05,479 --> 00:08:06,984
Take her away!

47
00:08:11,331 --> 00:08:13,632
Holding her is dangerous.
If word of this gets out,

48
00:08:13,657 --> 00:08:16,260
it could generate sympathy
for the rebellion in the Senate.

49
00:08:16,495 --> 00:08:19,003
I've traced the rebel spies to her.

50
00:08:19,127 --> 00:08:21,428
Now she is my only link
to finding their secret base.

51
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,714
She'll die before she'll tell you anything.

52
00:08:23,739 --> 00:08:24,701
Leave that to me.

53
00:08:25,402 --> 00:08:29,114
Send a distress signal and then inform
the Senate that all aboard were killed.

54
00:08:29,139 --> 00:08:32,431
Lord Vader, the battle station plans
are not aboard this ship,

55
00:08:32,456 --> 00:08:34,262
and no transmissions were made.

56
00:08:34,379 --> 00:08:36,794
An escape pod was jettisoned
during the fighting,

57
00:08:36,818 --> 00:08:38,085
but no life forms were aboard.

58
00:08:38,558 --> 00:08:40,999
She must have hidden the plans
in the escape pod.

59
00:08:41,024 --> 00:08:44,866
Send a detachment down to retrieve them.
See to it personally, Commander.

60
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:47,094
There'll be no one to stop us this time.

61
00:08:47,118 --> 00:08:48,279
Yes, sir.

62
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,277
How did we get into this mess?

63
00:09:05,377 --> 00:09:07,741
I really don't know how.

64
00:09:08,413 --> 00:09:11,313
We seem to be made to suffer.
It's our lot in life.

65
00:09:14,405 --> 00:09:17,805
I've got to rest before I fall apart.
My joints are almost frozen.

66
00:09:25,063 --> 00:09:27,563
What a desolate place this is!

67
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,339
Where do you think you're going?

68
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:35,281
Well, I'm not going that way.

69
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,991
It's much too rocky.

70
00:09:37,581 --> 00:09:39,106
This way is much easier.

71
00:09:39,676 --> 00:09:41,716
What makes you think
there are settlements over there?

72
00:09:44,078 --> 00:09:45,978
Don't get technical with me.

73
00:09:46,979 --> 00:09:48,884
What mission? What are you talking about?

74
00:09:51,155 --> 00:09:53,455
I've just about had enough of you.

75
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,386
Go that way.

76
00:09:55,417 --> 00:09:58,246
You'll be malfunctioning within a day,
you nearsighted scrap pile.

77
00:09:59,251 --> 00:10:03,053
And don't let me catch you following me
begging for help, because you won't get it.

78
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:20,230
No more adventures.
I'm not going that way.

79
00:10:54,948 --> 00:10:58,649
That malfunctioning little twerp.
This is all his fault.

80
00:10:58,881 --> 00:11:02,510
He tricked me into going this way,
but he'll do no better.

81
00:11:06,605 --> 00:11:08,403
Wait! What's that?

82
00:11:08,427 --> 00:11:11,043
A transport! I'm saved!

83
00:11:11,356 --> 00:11:14,856
Over here!
Hey! Hey!

84
00:11:16,015 --> 00:11:19,542
Help! Please help!

85
00:14:49,547 --> 00:14:50,714
R2?

86
00:14:54,332 --> 00:14:57,532
R2-D2, it is you! It is you!

87
00:15:15,766 --> 00:15:19,480
Someone was in the pod.
The tracks go off in this direction.

88
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:21,854
Look, sir. Droids.

89
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:35,666
Wake up! Wake up!

90
00:15:42,373 --> 00:15:44,373
We're doomed.

91
00:15:52,289 --> 00:15:54,989
Do you think they'll melt us down?

92
00:16:07,112 --> 00:16:08,819
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

93
00:16:09,261 --> 00:16:11,261
Will this never end?

94
00:16:51,293 --> 00:16:52,848
All right, fine. Let's go.

95
00:16:52,873 --> 00:16:55,034
Luke! Luke!

96
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:03,650
Luke, tell Uncle if he gets a translator,
be sure it speaks Bocce.

97
00:17:03,862 --> 00:17:07,262
Doesn't look like we have much
of a choice, but I'll remind him.

98
00:17:17,768 --> 00:17:20,768
Yeah, we'll take that red one.
No, not that one.

99
00:17:23,635 --> 00:17:26,489
You, I suppose you're programmed
for etiquette and protocol.

100
00:17:26,783 --> 00:17:29,290
Protocol? Why, it's my
primary function, sir.

101
00:17:29,334 --> 00:17:30,699
I am well-versed in all the customs—

102
00:17:30,724 --> 00:17:32,656
I have no need
for a protocol droid.

103
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,626
Of course you haven't, sir.

104
00:17:33,651 --> 00:17:36,555
Not in an environment such as this.
That is why I have been programmed—

105
00:17:36,655 --> 00:17:41,041
What I really need is a droid who understands
the binary language of moisture vaporators.

106
00:17:41,066 --> 00:17:44,519
Vaporators? Sir, my first job
was programming binary load lifters,

107
00:17:44,544 --> 00:17:46,758
very similar to your vaporators
in most respects.

108
00:17:46,783 --> 00:17:47,760
Can you speak Bocce?

109
00:17:47,784 --> 00:17:50,353
Of course I can, sir. It's like a
second language to me. I'm as fluent—

110
00:17:50,377 --> 00:17:53,103
Yeah, all right. Shut up.
I'll take this one. Luke!

111
00:17:56,197 --> 00:17:58,948
Take these two over to the garage, will you?
I want them cleaned up before dinner.

112
00:17:58,973 --> 00:18:01,621
But I was going into Tosche Station
to pick up some power converters.

113
00:18:01,928 --> 00:18:04,723
You can waste time with your friends
when your chores are done.

114
00:18:04,748 --> 00:18:06,185
Now come on. Get to it.

115
00:18:08,076 --> 00:18:09,839
All right. Come on.

116
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:13,949
And the red one. Come on.

117
00:18:15,147 --> 00:18:17,106
Well, come on, red. Let's go.

118
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:37,946
Uncle Owen!

119
00:18:37,971 --> 00:18:38,886
Yeah?

120
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,481
This R2 unit has a bad motivator. Look.

121
00:18:41,966 --> 00:18:44,227
Hey, what are you trying to push on us?

122
00:18:47,117 --> 00:18:48,557
Excuse me, sir,

123
00:18:48,581 --> 00:18:51,641
but that R2 unit is in prime condition,
a real bargain.

124
00:18:52,170 --> 00:18:54,572
Uncle Owen, what about that one?

125
00:18:54,599 --> 00:18:57,274
What about that blue one?
We'll take that one.

126
00:18:58,303 --> 00:18:59,326
Yeah, take this away.

127
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,896
You'll be very pleased
with that one, sir.

128
00:19:00,921 --> 00:19:03,891
He really is in first-class condition.
I've worked with him before.

129
00:19:04,405 --> 00:19:05,738
Here he comes.

130
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:11,042
Okay, let's go.

131
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,425
Now, don't you forget this.

132
00:19:12,449 --> 00:19:15,986
Why I should stick my neck out for you
is quite beyond my capacity.

133
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:26,129
Thank the maker!
This oil bath is going to feel so good.

134
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:30,600
I've got such a bad case
of dust contamination, I can barely move.

135
00:19:30,889 --> 00:19:35,531
It just isn't fair. Oh, Biggs is right.
I'm never gonna get out of here.

136
00:19:35,941 --> 00:19:38,006
Is there anything I might do to help?

137
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:40,780
No. Not unless you can alter time,

138
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:43,242
speed up the harvest,
or teleport me off this rock.

139
00:19:43,448 --> 00:19:44,889
I don't think so, sir.

140
00:19:44,913 --> 00:19:47,686
I'm only a droid, and not very
knowledgeable about such things.

141
00:19:48,045 --> 00:19:49,797
Not on this planet, anyway.

142
00:19:49,821 --> 00:19:53,025
 As a matter of fact,
I'm not even sure which planet I'm on.

143
00:19:53,296 --> 00:19:57,767
Well, if there's a bright center to the universe,
you're on the planet that it's farthest from.

144
00:19:57,985 --> 00:19:59,111
I see, sir.

145
00:20:00,465 --> 00:20:01,574
You can call me Luke.

146
00:20:01,599 --> 00:20:03,022
I see, Sir Luke.

147
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:05,386
Just Luke.

148
00:20:05,411 --> 00:20:06,106
Oh.

149
00:20:06,565 --> 00:20:09,801
And I am C-3PO,
human-cyborg relations.

150
00:20:09,871 --> 00:20:12,028
And this is my
counterpart, R2-D2.

151
00:20:12,709 --> 00:20:13,964
Hello.

152
00:20:15,379 --> 00:20:17,214
You've got a lot of carbon scoring here,

153
00:20:17,238 --> 00:20:18,650
looks like you boys have
seen a lot of action.

154
00:20:18,825 --> 00:20:20,102
With all we've been through,

155
00:20:20,126 --> 00:20:22,629
sometimes I'm amazed we're in
as good condition as we are,

156
00:20:22,653 --> 00:20:24,000
what with the rebellion and all.

157
00:20:24,261 --> 00:20:25,985
You know of the rebellion
against the Empire?!

158
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:29,230
That's how we came to be in your service,
if you take my meaning, sir.

159
00:20:29,825 --> 00:20:30,929
Have you been in many battles?

160
00:20:30,953 --> 00:20:31,926
Several, I think.

161
00:20:32,213 --> 00:20:34,215
Actually, there's not much to tell.

162
00:20:34,239 --> 00:20:37,779
I'm not much more than an interpreter,
and not very good at telling stories.

163
00:20:37,803 --> 00:20:40,169
Well, not at making them
interesting, anyway.

164
00:20:41,166 --> 00:20:45,101
Well, my little friend, you've got something
jammed in here real good.

165
00:20:45,444 --> 00:20:47,244
Were you on a Starcruiser or—

166
00:20:47,545 --> 00:20:50,719
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.
You're my only hope.</i>

167
00:20:50,744 --> 00:20:52,053
What's this?

168
00:20:52,550 --> 00:20:53,536
“What is what?”

169
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,521
He asked you a question.
What is that?

170
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:59,316
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.
You're my only hope.</i>

171
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:06,440
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.
You're my only hope.</i>

172
00:21:09,060 --> 00:21:10,708
Oh. He says it's nothing, sir.

173
00:21:10,732 --> 00:21:13,505
Merely a malfunction, old data.
Pay it no mind.

174
00:21:13,787 --> 00:21:16,008
Who is she?
She's beautiful.

175
00:21:16,228 --> 00:21:19,478
I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir.

176
00:21:19,673 --> 00:21:22,055
I think she was a passenger
on our last voyage.

177
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,299
A person of some importances,
I believe.

178
00:21:24,323 --> 00:21:25,331
Our captain was attached to—

179
00:21:25,356 --> 00:21:27,456
Is there any more to this recording?

180
00:21:28,731 --> 00:21:31,603
Behave yourself, R2.
You're going to get us into trouble.

181
00:21:31,925 --> 00:21:34,799
It's all right. You can trust him.
He's our new master.

182
00:21:37,923 --> 00:21:40,864
He says that he's the property
of Obi-Wan Kenobi,

183
00:21:40,889 --> 00:21:44,236
a resident of these parts,
and it's a private message for him.

184
00:21:44,336 --> 00:21:46,486
Quite frankly, sir, I don't know what
he's talking about.

185
00:21:46,692 --> 00:21:48,774
Our last master was Captain Antilles.

186
00:21:48,798 --> 00:21:52,426
But with all we've been through,
this little R2 unit has become a bit eccentric.

187
00:21:53,736 --> 00:21:56,381
Obi-Wan Kenobi.
I wonder if he means old Ben Kenobi.

188
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:59,151
I beg your pardon, sir, but do you know
what he's talking about?

189
00:21:59,251 --> 00:22:01,747
Well, I don't know anyone
named Obi-Wan, but

190
00:22:02,665 --> 00:22:04,743
old Ben lives out beyond the Dune Sea.

191
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,000
He's kind of a strange old hermit.

192
00:22:07,593 --> 00:22:09,689
I wonder who she is.

193
00:22:09,962 --> 00:22:12,787
Sounds like she's in trouble,
I better play back the whole thing.

194
00:22:16,458 --> 00:22:19,658
He says the restraining bolt
has short-circuited his recording system.

195
00:22:20,332 --> 00:22:22,419
He suggests that if you remove the bolt,

196
00:22:22,444 --> 00:22:24,504
he might be able to play back
the entire recording.

197
00:22:24,529 --> 00:22:26,765
Hm? Oh, yeah. Well...

198
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:32,974
I guess you're too small to run away
on me if I take this off. Okay...

199
00:22:35,420 --> 00:22:37,220
There you go.

200
00:22:38,756 --> 00:22:41,782
Wait a minute. Where'd she go?
Bring her back. Play back the entire message.

201
00:22:42,383 --> 00:22:43,674
“What message?”

202
00:22:44,154 --> 00:22:45,460
The one you've just been playing!

203
00:22:45,485 --> 00:22:47,611
The one you're carrying
inside your rusty innards.

204
00:22:47,771 --> 00:22:49,626
Luke! Luke!

205
00:22:50,301 --> 00:22:52,515
All right, I'll be right there,
Aunt Beru.

206
00:22:52,539 --> 00:22:55,641
I'm sorry, sir, but he appears
to have picked up a slight flutter.

207
00:22:55,811 --> 00:22:59,170
Here. See what you can do with him.
I'll be right back.

208
00:23:01,901 --> 00:23:04,501
Just you reconsider
playing that message for him.

209
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:08,000
No, I don't think he likes you at all.

210
00:23:08,486 --> 00:23:10,522
No, I don't like you, either.

211
00:23:19,449 --> 00:23:22,065
You know, I think that R2 unit
we bought might have been stolen.

212
00:23:22,575 --> 00:23:23,843
What makes you think that?

213
00:23:23,868 --> 00:23:26,052
Well, I stumbled across a recording
while I was cleaning him.

214
00:23:26,116 --> 00:23:28,918
He says he belongs to someone
called Obi-Wan Kenobi.

215
00:23:31,609 --> 00:23:33,649
I thought he might have meant old Ben.

216
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,209
Do you know what he's talking about?

217
00:23:35,234 --> 00:23:36,023
Mm-mmm.

218
00:23:36,869 --> 00:23:39,345
I wonder if he's related to Ben.

219
00:23:39,370 --> 00:23:41,399
That wizard's just a crazy old man.

220
00:23:42,452 --> 00:23:46,080
Tomorrow, I want you to take that R2 unit
to Anchorhead and have its memory erased.

221
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:48,703
That'll be the end of it.
It belongs to us now.

222
00:23:50,161 --> 00:23:52,988
But what if this Obi-Wan
comes looking for him?

223
00:23:53,154 --> 00:23:54,077
He won't.

224
00:23:54,982 --> 00:23:56,670
 I don't think he exists anymore.

225
00:23:57,292 --> 00:23:59,245
He died about the same time
as your father.

226
00:23:59,270 --> 00:24:00,644
He knew my father?

227
00:24:01,083 --> 00:24:02,070
I told you to forget it.

228
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:06,093
Your only concern is to prepare
those new droids for tomorrow.

229
00:24:06,713 --> 00:24:08,510
In the morning, I want them
up there on the south ridge,

230
00:24:08,535 --> 00:24:10,013
working on those condensers.

231
00:24:10,676 --> 00:24:11,635
Yes, sir.

232
00:24:13,584 --> 00:24:15,665
I think those new droids
are gonna work out fine.

233
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:19,424
In fact, I, uh, was also thinking
about our agreement...

234
00:24:19,684 --> 00:24:21,727
about me staying on another season.

235
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:25,174
And if these new droids do work out,

236
00:24:25,198 --> 00:24:27,626
 I want to transmit my application
to the academy this year.

237
00:24:28,198 --> 00:24:30,258
You mean the next semester,
before the harvest?

238
00:24:30,282 --> 00:24:32,001
Sure. There's more than enough droids.

239
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,198
Harvest is when I need you the most.

240
00:24:34,222 --> 00:24:35,480
It's only one season more.

241
00:24:36,662 --> 00:24:39,572
This year we'll make enough on the harvest
that I'll be able to hire some more hands,

242
00:24:39,597 --> 00:24:41,512
and then you can go
to the academy next year.

243
00:24:42,710 --> 00:24:44,509
You must understand
I need you here, Luke.

244
00:24:44,842 --> 00:24:46,691
But it's a whole 'nother year!

245
00:24:46,741 --> 00:24:47,957
Look, it's only one more season.

246
00:24:47,989 --> 00:24:50,065
Yeah, that's what you said
when Biggs and Tank left.

247
00:24:50,125 --> 00:24:51,220
Where are you going?

248
00:24:51,284 --> 00:24:52,587
Looks like I'm going nowhere.

249
00:24:52,688 --> 00:24:54,531
I have to go finish cleaning those droids.

250
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,326
Owen, he can't stay here forever.

251
00:24:56,350 --> 00:24:58,079
Most of his friends have gone.

252
00:24:58,393 --> 00:25:00,096
It means so much to him.

253
00:25:00,508 --> 00:25:02,404
I'll make it up to him next year.

254
00:25:02,428 --> 00:25:03,282
I promise.

255
00:25:04,780 --> 00:25:06,947
Luke's just not a farmer, Owen.

256
00:25:06,971 --> 00:25:08,643
He has too much of his father in him.

257
00:25:09,474 --> 00:25:11,215
That's what I'm afraid of.

258
00:26:00,298 --> 00:26:02,059
What are you doing hiding back there?

259
00:26:02,084 --> 00:26:04,964
It wasn't my fault, sir.
Please don't deactivate me.

260
00:26:05,149 --> 00:26:07,810
I told him not to go,
but he's faulty, malfunctioning.

261
00:26:08,297 --> 00:26:10,271
Kept babbling on about his mission.

262
00:26:10,295 --> 00:26:11,801
Oh, no.

263
00:26:19,903 --> 00:26:22,677
That R2 unit has always been a problem.

264
00:26:22,745 --> 00:26:24,701
These astrodroids are getting
quite out of hand.

265
00:26:25,020 --> 00:26:27,278
Even I can't understand their logic at times.

266
00:26:27,324 --> 00:26:28,660
How could I be so stupid?

267
00:26:28,684 --> 00:26:31,037
He's nowhere in sight. Blast it!

268
00:26:31,635 --> 00:26:33,889
Pardon me, sir, but
couldn't we go after him?

269
00:26:33,913 --> 00:26:35,554
It's too dangerous with
all the Sand People around.

270
00:26:35,578 --> 00:26:36,933
We'll have to wait until morning.

271
00:26:36,958 --> 00:26:39,158
Luke! I'm shutting the power down.

272
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:41,376
All right!
I'll be there in a few minutes.

273
00:26:41,835 --> 00:26:43,176
Boy, am I gonna get it.

274
00:26:44,336 --> 00:26:46,206
You know, that little droid's gonna
cause me a lot of trouble.

275
00:26:46,231 --> 00:26:48,362
Oh, he excels at that, sir.

276
00:26:59,160 --> 00:26:59,899
Luke?

277
00:27:01,438 --> 00:27:02,225
Luke!

278
00:27:03,819 --> 00:27:04,613
Luke!

279
00:27:11,355 --> 00:27:12,732
Have you seen Luke this morning?

280
00:27:13,051 --> 00:27:15,360
He said he had some things to do
before he started today,

281
00:27:15,384 --> 00:27:16,454
so he left early.

282
00:27:16,513 --> 00:27:18,373
Did he take those two new droids with him?

283
00:27:18,486 --> 00:27:20,000
I think so.

284
00:27:20,375 --> 00:27:23,361
Well, he better have those units in the
south range repaired by midday,

285
00:27:23,385 --> 00:27:24,941
or there'll be hell to pay.

286
00:27:26,123 --> 00:27:28,493
Lookit, there's a droid on the scanner.
Dead ahead.

287
00:27:28,613 --> 00:27:31,741
It might be our little R2 unit.
Hit the accelerator!

288
00:27:54,037 --> 00:27:55,970
Hey, whoa! Just where do
you think you're going?

289
00:27:57,150 --> 00:27:59,164
Master Luke is your rightful owner now.

290
00:27:59,189 --> 00:28:02,101
We'll have no more of this
Obi-Wan Kenobi gibberish.

291
00:28:03,185 --> 00:28:05,053
And don't talk to me of
your mission, either.

292
00:28:05,199 --> 00:28:08,225
You're fortunate he doesn't blast you
into a million pieces right here!

293
00:28:08,249 --> 00:28:10,131
No. It's all right,
but I think we'd better go.

294
00:28:11,865 --> 00:28:13,444
What's wrong with him now?

295
00:28:13,505 --> 00:28:16,166
There are several creatures
approaching from the southeast.

296
00:28:16,931 --> 00:28:18,466
Sand People, or worse.

297
00:28:20,718 --> 00:28:22,318
Come on, let's go have a look.

298
00:28:22,342 --> 00:28:23,316
Come on!

299
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:29,731
Well, there are two Banthas down there.
But I don't see any...

300
00:28:29,975 --> 00:28:30,870
Wait a second.

301
00:28:31,888 --> 00:28:34,688
They're Sand People, all right.
I can see one of them now.

302
00:29:49,519 --> 00:29:50,686
Hello, there.

303
00:29:53,264 --> 00:29:55,074
Come here, my little friend.

304
00:29:55,558 --> 00:29:56,669
Don't be afraid.

305
00:29:59,012 --> 00:30:00,807
Oh, don't worry.
He'll be all right.

306
00:30:06,938 --> 00:30:09,551
Rest easy, son.
You've had a busy day.

307
00:30:10,138 --> 00:30:13,171
You're fortunate to be all in one piece.

308
00:30:16,446 --> 00:30:18,504
Ben?
Ben Kenobi?

309
00:30:19,063 --> 00:30:21,065
Boy, am I glad to see you.

310
00:30:21,231 --> 00:30:24,231
The Jundland Wastes
are not to be traveled lightly.

311
00:30:27,173 --> 00:30:28,761
Tell me, young Luke,

312
00:30:28,825 --> 00:30:31,113
what brings you out this far?

313
00:30:31,374 --> 00:30:33,108
This little droid.

314
00:30:34,832 --> 00:30:36,646
I think he's searching
for his former master,

315
00:30:36,670 --> 00:30:40,001
but I've never seen such devotion
 in a droid before.

316
00:30:40,879 --> 00:30:43,646
He claims to be the property
of an Obi-Wan Kenobi.

317
00:30:44,075 --> 00:30:46,777
Is he a relative of yours?
Do you know who he's talking about?

318
00:30:48,245 --> 00:30:50,655
Obi-Wan Kenobi?

319
00:30:52,225 --> 00:30:53,691
Obi-Wan.

320
00:30:54,724 --> 00:30:58,618
Now, that's a name
I've not heard in a long time.

321
00:30:59,268 --> 00:31:01,223
A long time.

322
00:31:02,420 --> 00:31:03,955
I think my uncle knows him.

323
00:31:04,101 --> 00:31:05,219
He said he was dead.

324
00:31:05,516 --> 00:31:08,312
Oh, he's not dead.
Not yet.

325
00:31:08,966 --> 00:31:10,193
You know him?

326
00:31:10,217 --> 00:31:12,936
Well, of course I know him.
He's me.

327
00:31:15,973 --> 00:31:19,375
I haven't gone by the name
of Obi-Wan since,

328
00:31:19,399 --> 00:31:21,445
oh, before you were born.

329
00:31:21,887 --> 00:31:23,689
Well, then the droid does belong to you.

330
00:31:23,714 --> 00:31:26,110
I don't seem to remember
ever owning a droid.

331
00:31:28,492 --> 00:31:30,147
Very interesting.

332
00:31:31,612 --> 00:31:34,128
I think we'd better get indoors.

333
00:31:34,152 --> 00:31:38,243
The Sand People are easily startled
but they'll soon be back,

334
00:31:38,267 --> 00:31:39,499
and in greater numbers.

335
00:31:42,467 --> 00:31:44,467
3PO.

336
00:31:53,418 --> 00:31:56,118
Where am I?
I must have taken a bad step.

337
00:31:57,895 --> 00:32:00,698
Can you stand? We've got to get out of here
before the Sand People return.

338
00:32:00,818 --> 00:32:03,321
I don't think I can make it.
You go on, Master Luke.

339
00:32:03,661 --> 00:32:06,238
There's no sense in you risking yourself
on my account.

340
00:32:06,390 --> 00:32:07,788
I'm done for.

341
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:10,670
No, you're not.
What kind of talk is that?

342
00:32:10,694 --> 00:32:12,457
Quickly. They're on the move.

343
00:32:17,935 --> 00:32:21,215
No, my father didn't fight in the wars.
He was a navigator on a spice freighter.

344
00:32:21,425 --> 00:32:23,194
That's what your uncle told you.

345
00:32:23,481 --> 00:32:25,258
He didn't hold with your father's ideals.

346
00:32:25,288 --> 00:32:28,342
Thought he should have stayed
here and not gotten involved.

347
00:32:29,054 --> 00:32:30,696
You fought in the Clone Wars?

348
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:35,509
Yes. I was once a Jedi knight,
the same as your father.

349
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:39,344
I wish I'd known him.

350
00:32:39,368 --> 00:32:42,555
He was the best starpilot
in the galaxy,

351
00:32:43,315 --> 00:32:44,708
and a cunning warrior.

352
00:32:45,029 --> 00:32:47,733
I understand you've become
quite a good pilot yourself.

353
00:32:49,900 --> 00:32:51,733
And he was a good friend.

354
00:32:52,952 --> 00:32:54,117
Which reminds me...

355
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,300
I have something here for you.

356
00:32:59,353 --> 00:33:02,281
Your father wanted you to have this
when you were old enough...

357
00:33:02,306 --> 00:33:04,687
but your uncle wouldn't allow it.

358
00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:10,043
He feared you might follow old Obi-Wan
on some damn-fool idealistic crusade,

359
00:33:10,068 --> 00:33:11,589
like your father did.

360
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:13,992
Sir, if you'll not be needing me,
I'll close down for a while.

361
00:33:14,092 --> 00:33:16,092
Sure. Go ahead.

362
00:33:18,505 --> 00:33:19,566
What is it?

363
00:33:19,806 --> 00:33:21,701
Your father's lightsaber.

364
00:33:22,666 --> 00:33:24,849
This is the weapon of a Jedi knight.

365
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:28,906
Not as clumsy or random as a blaster.

366
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:31,481
An elegant weapon

367
00:33:31,505 --> 00:33:35,245
for a more civilized age.

368
00:33:36,313 --> 00:33:37,849
For over a thousand generations,

369
00:33:37,873 --> 00:33:42,669
the Jedi knights were the guardians of
peace and justice in the old Republic...

370
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:45,928
Before the dark times.

371
00:33:45,952 --> 00:33:47,384
Before the Empire.

372
00:33:50,747 --> 00:33:52,433
How did my father die?

373
00:33:54,804 --> 00:33:57,173
A young Jedi named Darth Vader,

374
00:33:57,490 --> 00:34:00,316
who was a pupil of mine
until he turned to evil,

375
00:34:00,824 --> 00:34:03,985
helped the Empire hunt down
and destroy the Jedi knights.

376
00:34:05,943 --> 00:34:08,543
He betrayed and murdered your father.

377
00:34:10,198 --> 00:34:12,479
Now the Jedi are all but extinct.

378
00:34:13,737 --> 00:34:17,376
Vader was seduced
by the dark side of the Force.

379
00:34:18,322 --> 00:34:19,779
The Force?

380
00:34:20,410 --> 00:34:22,753
The Force is what gives a Jedi his power.

381
00:34:23,460 --> 00:34:26,131
It's an energy field created
by all living things.

382
00:34:26,231 --> 00:34:30,792
It surrounds us, penetrates us,
it binds the galaxy together.

383
00:34:38,167 --> 00:34:41,331
Now let's see if we can't figure out
what you are, my little friend,

384
00:34:41,722 --> 00:34:43,571
and where you come from.

385
00:34:43,841 --> 00:34:45,329
I saw part of a message he w—

386
00:34:45,353 --> 00:34:46,945
I seem to have found it.

387
00:34:47,185 --> 00:34:48,741
<i>General Kenobi,</i>

388
00:34:48,765 --> 00:34:51,451
<i> years ago you served my father
in the Clone Wars.</i>

389
00:34:51,922 --> 00:34:55,092
<i>Now he begs you to help him
in his struggle against the Empire.</i>

390
00:34:55,259 --> 00:34:58,196
<i>I regret that I am unable to present
my father's request to you in person.</i>

391
00:34:58,534 --> 00:35:00,139
<i>But my ship has fallen under attack,</i>

392
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:02,584
<i>and I am afraid my mission
to bring you to Alderaan has failed.</i>

393
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,179
<i>I have placed information
vital to the survival of the rebellion</i>

394
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:08,567
<i>into the memory
systems of this R2 unit.</i>

395
00:35:08,591 --> 00:35:10,004
<i>My father will know how to retrieve it.</i>

396
00:35:10,768 --> 00:35:14,023
<i>You must see this droid
safely delivered to him on Alderaan.</i>

397
00:35:14,739 --> 00:35:16,757
<i>This is our most desperate hour.</i>

398
00:35:17,239 --> 00:35:20,301
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.
You're my only hope.</i>

399
00:35:35,499 --> 00:35:39,431
You must learn the ways of the Force
if you're to come with me to Alderaan.

400
00:35:40,311 --> 00:35:41,119
Alderaan?

401
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:43,048
I'm not going to Alderaan.

402
00:35:43,073 --> 00:35:45,379
I've got to get home. It's late.
I'm in for it as it is.

403
00:35:45,404 --> 00:35:48,105
I need your help, Luke.
She needs your help.

404
00:35:48,579 --> 00:35:50,847
I'm getting too old for this sort of thing.

405
00:35:56,186 --> 00:35:57,779
I can't get involved.

406
00:35:58,065 --> 00:35:59,486
I've got work to do.

407
00:35:59,950 --> 00:36:02,064
It's not that I like the Empire.
I hate it, but

408
00:36:02,088 --> 00:36:04,450
there's nothing I can
do about it right now.

409
00:36:06,189 --> 00:36:07,529
It's all such a long way from here.

410
00:36:07,929 --> 00:36:09,723
That's your uncle talking.

411
00:36:10,407 --> 00:36:13,624
My uncle.
How am I ever gonna explain this?

412
00:36:13,870 --> 00:36:15,543
Learn about the Force, Luke.

413
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:24,823
Look, I can take you as far as Anchorhead.

414
00:36:25,182 --> 00:36:28,868
You can get a transport there to
Mos Eisley or wherever you're going.

415
00:36:29,886 --> 00:36:32,477
You must do what you feel
is right, of course.

416
00:36:40,551 --> 00:36:43,820
Until this battle station is fully
operational, we are vulnerable.

417
00:36:44,580 --> 00:36:46,635
The Rebel Alliance is too well equipped.

418
00:36:46,659 --> 00:36:48,295
They're more dangerous than you realize.

419
00:36:48,912 --> 00:36:51,312
Dangerous to your starfleet, Commander.

420
00:36:51,336 --> 00:36:53,043
Not to this battle station.

421
00:36:53,477 --> 00:36:56,968
The rebellion will continue to gain support
in the Imperial Senate—

422
00:36:56,993 --> 00:37:00,697
The Imperial Senate will no longer
be of any concern to us.

423
00:37:01,272 --> 00:37:05,314
I have just received word that the Emperor
has dissolved the council permanently.

424
00:37:05,779 --> 00:37:09,627
The last remnants of the old Republic
have been swept away.

425
00:37:09,922 --> 00:37:11,427
That's impossible.

426
00:37:11,695 --> 00:37:14,264
How will the Emperor maintain control
without the bureaucracy?

427
00:37:14,291 --> 00:37:18,491
The regional governors now have
direct control over their territories.

428
00:37:19,182 --> 00:37:22,543
Fear will keep the local systems in line...

429
00:37:23,055 --> 00:37:24,750
Fear of this battle station.

430
00:37:24,774 --> 00:37:26,144
And what of the rebellion?

431
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:29,495
If the rebels have obtained a complete
technical readout of this station,

432
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:31,564
it is possible, however unlikely,

433
00:37:31,588 --> 00:37:34,306
that they might find a weakness
and exploit it.

434
00:37:34,551 --> 00:37:38,117
The plans you refer to will
soon be back in our hands.

435
00:37:38,489 --> 00:37:42,545
Any attack made by the rebels against
this station would be a useless gesture,

436
00:37:42,569 --> 00:37:44,544
no matter what technical data
they've obtained.

437
00:37:44,942 --> 00:37:48,405
This station is now the ultimate power
in the universe.

438
00:37:49,032 --> 00:37:50,932
I suggest we use it.

439
00:37:51,161 --> 00:37:54,394
Don't be too proud of this
technological terror you've constructed.

440
00:37:55,278 --> 00:37:58,503
The ability to destroy a planet
is insignificant

441
00:37:58,528 --> 00:38:00,444
next to the power of the Force.

442
00:38:00,630 --> 00:38:04,088
Don't try to frighten us with
your sorcerer's ways, Lord Vader.

443
00:38:04,434 --> 00:38:06,837
Your sad devotion
to that ancient religion

444
00:38:06,868 --> 00:38:09,767
has not helped you conjure up
the stolen data tapes,

445
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:14,052
or given you clairvoyance enough
to find the rebels' hidden fortr—

446
00:38:20,664 --> 00:38:22,864
I find your lack of faith disturbing.

447
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:27,397
Enough of this.
Vader, release him.

448
00:38:27,671 --> 00:38:29,371
As you wish.

449
00:38:31,422 --> 00:38:33,422
This bickering is pointless.

450
00:38:34,657 --> 00:38:38,257
Lord Vader will provide us with
the location of the rebel fortress

451
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:40,434
by the time this station is operational.

452
00:38:41,158 --> 00:38:44,469
We will then crush the rebellion
with one swift stroke.

453
00:38:52,096 --> 00:38:53,973
It looks like the Sand People
did this, all right.

454
00:38:53,998 --> 00:38:55,733
Look. There's gaffi sticks, Bantha tracks.

455
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:58,302
It's just, I've never heard of them
hitting anything this big before.

456
00:38:58,402 --> 00:38:59,534
They didn't...

457
00:38:59,558 --> 00:39:01,772
but we are meant
to think they did.

458
00:39:01,872 --> 00:39:03,797
These tracks are side-by-side.

459
00:39:03,821 --> 00:39:07,849
Sand People always ride single file
to hide their numbers.

460
00:39:08,111 --> 00:39:10,847
These are the same Jawas
that sold us R2 and 3PO.

461
00:39:10,914 --> 00:39:15,173
And these blast points,
too accurate for Sand People.

462
00:39:15,919 --> 00:39:19,048
Only Imperial stormtroopers
are so precise.

463
00:39:19,902 --> 00:39:22,634
But why would Imperial troops
want to slaughter Jawas?

464
00:39:27,864 --> 00:39:30,401
If they traced the robots here, they
may have learned who they sold them to,

465
00:39:30,426 --> 00:39:32,701
and that would lead them back... home!

466
00:39:33,149 --> 00:39:36,118
Wait, Luke!
It's too dangerous!

467
00:40:00,557 --> 00:40:04,061
Uncle Owen!
Aunt Beru!

468
00:40:04,201 --> 00:40:06,301
Uncle Owen!

469
00:40:55,218 --> 00:41:00,520
And now, Your Highness, we will discuss
the location of your hidden rebel base.

470
00:41:43,446 --> 00:41:46,346
There's nothing you could
have done, Luke, had you been there.

471
00:41:46,836 --> 00:41:48,741
You'd have been killed, too,

472
00:41:48,765 --> 00:41:51,400
and the droids would now be
in the hands of the Empire.

473
00:41:53,275 --> 00:41:55,475
I want to come with you to Alderaan.

474
00:41:56,052 --> 00:41:57,620
There's nothing for me here now.

475
00:41:58,166 --> 00:42:01,883
I want to learn the ways of the Force
and become a Jedi like my father.

476
00:42:16,793 --> 00:42:19,060
Mos Eisley spaceport.

477
00:42:19,469 --> 00:42:24,436
You will never find a more
wretched hive of scum and villainy.

478
00:42:25,094 --> 00:42:26,811
We must be cautious.

479
00:42:43,019 --> 00:42:44,301
How long have you had these droids?

480
00:42:44,325 --> 00:42:45,666
About three or four seasons.

481
00:42:45,749 --> 00:42:47,906
They're up for sale if you want them.

482
00:42:48,831 --> 00:42:50,230
Let me see your identification.

483
00:42:50,254 --> 00:42:52,767
You don't need to see his identification.

484
00:42:53,962 --> 00:42:55,449
We don't need to see his identification.

485
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:57,805
These aren't the droids
you're looking for.

486
00:42:58,941 --> 00:43:00,957
These aren't the droids we're looking for.

487
00:43:01,210 --> 00:43:03,410
He can go about his business.

488
00:43:04,326 --> 00:43:05,419
You can go about your business.

489
00:43:05,443 --> 00:43:06,852
Move along.

490
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:09,836
Move along.
Move along.

491
00:43:20,803 --> 00:43:23,843
I can't abide those Jawas.
Disgusting creatures!

492
00:43:25,001 --> 00:43:26,901
Go on, go on.

493
00:43:28,277 --> 00:43:30,044
I can't understand how we
got by those troops.

494
00:43:30,068 --> 00:43:31,447
 I thought we were dead.

495
00:43:31,608 --> 00:43:35,812
The Force can have a strong influence
on the weak-minded.

496
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:42,552
Do you really think we're gonna find a pilot
here that'll take us to Alderaan?

497
00:43:42,577 --> 00:43:45,047
Most of the best freighter pilots
are to be found here,

498
00:43:45,078 --> 00:43:47,023
only watch your step.

499
00:43:47,047 --> 00:43:48,790
This place can
be a little rough.

500
00:43:49,226 --> 00:43:50,828
I'm ready for anything.

501
00:43:54,831 --> 00:43:56,731
Come along, R2.

502
00:44:46,922 --> 00:44:49,668
Hey! We don't serve their kind here.

503
00:44:49,944 --> 00:44:50,456
What?

504
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:53,790
Your droids, they'll have to wait outside.
We don't want them here.

505
00:44:53,843 --> 00:44:56,020
Why don't you wait out by the speeder?
We don't want any trouble.

506
00:44:56,126 --> 00:44:58,026
I heartily agree with you, sir.

507
00:45:07,871 --> 00:45:09,571
I'll have one of those.

508
00:45:44,974 --> 00:45:46,302
He doesn't like you.

509
00:45:46,326 --> 00:45:47,520
I'm sorry.

510
00:45:49,100 --> 00:45:51,111
I don't like you, either.

511
00:45:51,467 --> 00:45:54,170
You just watch yourself.
We're wanted men.

512
00:45:54,194 --> 00:45:57,252
I have the death sentence
on 12 systems.

513
00:45:57,513 --> 00:45:58,731
I'll be careful.

514
00:45:59,309 --> 00:46:00,332
You'll be dead!

515
00:46:00,356 --> 00:46:02,678
This little one's not worth the effort.

516
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:05,069
Come, let me get you something.

517
00:46:08,146 --> 00:46:09,946
No blasters! No blasters!

518
00:46:32,228 --> 00:46:33,928
I'm all right.

519
00:46:35,619 --> 00:46:39,672
Chewbacca here is first mate
on a ship that might suit us.

520
00:46:44,605 --> 00:46:46,705
I don't like the look of this.

521
00:47:01,377 --> 00:47:02,779
Han Solo.

522
00:47:02,803 --> 00:47:04,677
I'm captain of the <i>Millennium Falcon</i>.

523
00:47:05,122 --> 00:47:08,522
Chewie here tells me you're looking
for passage to the Alderaan system.

524
00:47:08,625 --> 00:47:10,933
Yes, indeed, if it's a fast ship.

525
00:47:11,127 --> 00:47:12,566
Fast ship?

526
00:47:12,590 --> 00:47:14,603
You've never heard of the
<i>Millennium Falcon</i>?

527
00:47:15,256 --> 00:47:16,449
Should I have?

528
00:47:16,474 --> 00:47:19,784
It's the ship that made the Kessel run
in less than 12 parsecs.

529
00:47:21,596 --> 00:47:23,849
I've outrun Imperial starships.

530
00:47:24,028 --> 00:47:25,776
Not the local bulk cruisers, mind you.

531
00:47:25,802 --> 00:47:28,322
I'm talking about the big
Corellian ships now.

532
00:47:30,233 --> 00:47:32,463
She's fast enough for you, old man.

533
00:47:33,099 --> 00:47:34,178
What's the cargo?

534
00:47:34,281 --> 00:47:35,478
Only passengers.

535
00:47:36,057 --> 00:47:39,028
Myself, the boy, two droids,

536
00:47:39,962 --> 00:47:42,062
and no questions asked.

537
00:47:43,479 --> 00:47:45,482
What is it, some kind of local trouble?

538
00:47:45,562 --> 00:47:50,191
Let's just say we'd like to avoid
any Imperial entanglements.

539
00:47:51,834 --> 00:47:54,320
Well, that's the real trick, isn't it?

540
00:47:55,104 --> 00:47:57,195
And it's gonna cost you something extra.

541
00:47:58,474 --> 00:48:00,774
Ten thousand, all in advance.

542
00:48:01,845 --> 00:48:03,745
Ten thousand?

543
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:06,693
We could almost buy our own ship for that!

544
00:48:07,150 --> 00:48:09,517
But who's gonna fly it, kid? You?

545
00:48:09,541 --> 00:48:11,577
You bet I could.
I'm not such a bad pilot myself.

546
00:48:11,601 --> 00:48:13,989
We don't have to sit here and listen...

547
00:48:14,883 --> 00:48:17,087
We can pay you two thousand now,

548
00:48:17,167 --> 00:48:20,227
plus fifteen when we reach Alderaan.

549
00:48:21,397 --> 00:48:23,097
Seventeen, huh?

550
00:48:26,020 --> 00:48:28,324
Okay, you guys got yourselves a ship.

551
00:48:28,464 --> 00:48:31,026
We'll leave as soon as you're ready.
Docking Bay 94.

552
00:48:31,373 --> 00:48:32,838
Ninety-four.

553
00:48:33,796 --> 00:48:38,401
Looks like somebody's beginning to
take an interest in your handiwork.

554
00:48:38,682 --> 00:48:40,809
All right. We'll check it out.

555
00:48:52,848 --> 00:48:54,849
Seventeen thousand!

556
00:48:54,949 --> 00:48:57,854
Those guys must really be desperate.
This could really save my neck.

557
00:48:57,879 --> 00:49:00,549
Get back to the ship, get it ready.

558
00:49:00,879 --> 00:49:02,447
You'll have to sell your speeder.

559
00:49:02,502 --> 00:49:06,065
That's okay. I'm never coming back
to this planet again.

560
00:49:08,601 --> 00:49:11,305
Yes, Greedo. As a matter of fact,
I was just going to see your boss.

561
00:49:11,838 --> 00:49:13,738
Tell Jabba that I've got his money.

562
00:49:27,300 --> 00:49:29,569
Yeah, but this time I've got the money.

563
00:49:33,839 --> 00:49:36,139
I don't have it with me. Tell Jabba—

564
00:49:46,210 --> 00:49:48,512
Even I get boarded sometimes.
Do you think I had a choice?

565
00:49:53,411 --> 00:49:54,879
Over my dead body.

566
00:50:00,466 --> 00:50:02,366
Yes, I'll bet you have.

567
00:50:15,888 --> 00:50:17,888
Sorry about the mess.

568
00:50:26,692 --> 00:50:29,663
Her resistance to the mind probe
is considerable.

569
00:50:29,763 --> 00:50:32,857
It'll be some time before we can
extract any information from her.

570
00:50:33,439 --> 00:50:35,268
The final checkout is completed.

571
00:50:35,368 --> 00:50:38,537
All systems are operational.
What course shall we set?

572
00:50:39,345 --> 00:50:42,715
Perhaps she would respond
to an alternative form of persuasion.

573
00:50:43,168 --> 00:50:44,427
What do you mean?

574
00:50:44,452 --> 00:50:47,548
I think it is time we demonstrated
the full power of this station.

575
00:50:47,641 --> 00:50:49,030
Set your course for Alderaan.

576
00:50:49,127 --> 00:50:50,100
With pleasure.

577
00:50:51,449 --> 00:50:53,449
Lock the door, R2.

578
00:50:55,560 --> 00:50:57,860
All right, check this side of the street.

579
00:51:01,727 --> 00:51:04,190
The door's locked.
Move on to the next one.

580
00:51:11,099 --> 00:51:14,466
I would much rather have gone
with Master Luke than stay here with you.

581
00:51:14,547 --> 00:51:17,739
I don't know what all this trouble is about,
but I'm sure it must be your fault.

582
00:51:18,659 --> 00:51:20,751
You watch your language.

583
00:51:22,815 --> 00:51:25,652
All right. Give it to me.
I'll take it.

584
00:51:25,752 --> 00:51:27,016
Look at this.

585
00:51:27,040 --> 00:51:29,356
Ever since the XP-38 came out,
 they just aren't in demand.

586
00:51:29,395 --> 00:51:30,920
It'll be enough.

587
00:51:48,575 --> 00:51:52,075
If the ship's as fast as he's boasting,
we ought to do well.

588
00:52:14,800 --> 00:52:16,402
What a piece of junk!

589
00:52:16,502 --> 00:52:18,632
She'll make .5 past light speed.

590
00:52:18,980 --> 00:52:21,927
She may not look like much,
but she's got it where it counts, kid.

591
00:52:21,952 --> 00:52:24,655
I've made a lot of special
modifications myself.

592
00:52:24,957 --> 00:52:26,232
But we're a little rushed,

593
00:52:26,256 --> 00:52:28,937
so if you'll just get on board,
we'll get outta here.

594
00:52:34,086 --> 00:52:35,412
Hello, sir.

595
00:52:43,849 --> 00:52:45,316
Which way?

596
00:52:47,216 --> 00:52:49,266
All right, men, load your weapons.

597
00:52:51,476 --> 00:52:53,570
Stop that ship!
Blast them!

598
00:53:03,281 --> 00:53:05,382
Chewie, get us out of here!

599
00:53:06,618 --> 00:53:09,984
Oh, my. I'd forgotten how much
I hate space travel.

600
00:53:25,552 --> 00:53:26,986
Looks like an Imperial cruiser.

601
00:53:27,011 --> 00:53:29,643
Our passengers must be hotter
than I thought. Try and hold 'em off.

602
00:53:29,668 --> 00:53:33,669
Angle the deflector shields while I make
the calculations for the jump to light speed.

603
00:53:43,489 --> 00:53:46,326
Stay sharp. There's two more coming in.
They're gonna try and cut us off.

604
00:53:46,426 --> 00:53:48,400
Why don't you outrun 'em?
I thought you said this thing was fast!

605
00:53:48,425 --> 00:53:50,896
Watch your mouth, kid, or you're
gonna find yourself floating home.

606
00:53:50,996 --> 00:53:53,900
We'll be safe enough once we
make the jump to hyperspace.

607
00:53:53,979 --> 00:53:56,179
Besides, I know a few maneuvers.
We'll lose 'em.

608
00:54:00,673 --> 00:54:02,133
Here's where the fun begins.

609
00:54:02,233 --> 00:54:04,277
How long before you can make
the jump to light speed?

610
00:54:04,377 --> 00:54:07,013
It'll take a few moments to get
the coordinates from the navicomputer.

611
00:54:07,113 --> 00:54:08,948
Are you kidding?
At the rate they're gaining?

612
00:54:09,048 --> 00:54:11,818
Traveling through hyperspace
ain't like dustin' crops, boy!

613
00:54:11,971 --> 00:54:14,273
Without precise calculations,
we'd fly right through a star,

614
00:54:14,298 --> 00:54:15,863
or bounce too close to a supernova,

615
00:54:15,894 --> 00:54:18,363
and that would end your trip
real quick, wouldn't it?

616
00:54:18,457 --> 00:54:19,450
What's that flashing?

617
00:54:19,474 --> 00:54:20,573
We're losing a deflector shield.

618
00:54:20,598 --> 00:54:23,398
Go strap yourselves in.
I'm gonna make the jump to light speed.

619
00:54:45,050 --> 00:54:47,250
We've entered the Alderaan system.

620
00:54:47,819 --> 00:54:49,318
Governor Tarkin.

621
00:54:49,342 --> 00:54:51,757
I should have expected to find you
holding Vader's leash.

622
00:54:52,330 --> 00:54:55,590
I recognized your foul stench
when I was brought on board.

623
00:54:57,096 --> 00:54:58,896
Charming to the last.

624
00:54:59,905 --> 00:55:03,811
You don't know how hard I found it,
signing the order to terminate your life.

625
00:55:03,836 --> 00:55:06,773
I'm surprised you had the courage
to take the responsibility yourself.

626
00:55:07,198 --> 00:55:10,039
Princess Leia, before your execution,

627
00:55:10,063 --> 00:55:11,486
I would like you to be my guest

628
00:55:11,511 --> 00:55:15,140
at a ceremony that will make
this battle station operational.

629
00:55:15,473 --> 00:55:18,301
No star system will dare
oppose the Emperor now.

630
00:55:18,893 --> 00:55:21,128
The more you tighten your grip, Tarkin,

631
00:55:21,153 --> 00:55:23,723
the more star systems
will slip through your fingers.

632
00:55:23,943 --> 00:55:26,706
Not after we demonstrate
the power of this station.

633
00:55:27,221 --> 00:55:30,845
In a way, you have determined
the choice of the planet

634
00:55:30,869 --> 00:55:32,262
that will be destroyed first.

635
00:55:33,132 --> 00:55:37,437
Since you are reluctant to provide us
with the location of the rebel base,

636
00:55:37,537 --> 00:55:40,420
I have chosen to test this station's
destructive power

637
00:55:40,445 --> 00:55:43,409
on your home planet of Alderaan.

638
00:55:43,509 --> 00:55:46,220
No! Alderaan is peaceful.
We have no weapons. You can't possibly—

639
00:55:46,245 --> 00:55:48,957
You would prefer another target?
A military target?

640
00:55:48,981 --> 00:55:50,972
Then name the system.

641
00:55:53,085 --> 00:55:56,286
I grow tired of asking this,
so it will be the last time.

642
00:55:57,162 --> 00:55:59,262
Where is the rebel base?

643
00:56:03,114 --> 00:56:04,914
Dantooine.

644
00:56:05,564 --> 00:56:06,830
They're on Dantooine.

645
00:56:06,854 --> 00:56:08,401
There. You see, Lord Vader?

646
00:56:08,426 --> 00:56:10,345
She can be reasonable.

647
00:56:10,369 --> 00:56:12,924
Continue with the operation.
You may fire when ready.

648
00:56:13,159 --> 00:56:13,950
What?

649
00:56:13,974 --> 00:56:15,367
You're far too trusting.

650
00:56:15,707 --> 00:56:18,313
Dantooine is too remote to make
an effective demonstration,

651
00:56:18,344 --> 00:56:19,400
but don't worry.

652
00:56:19,425 --> 00:56:22,328
We will deal with your rebel friends
soon enough.

653
00:56:22,481 --> 00:56:23,981
No!

654
00:56:25,751 --> 00:56:27,751
<i>Commence primary ignition.</i>

655
00:56:50,676 --> 00:56:53,577
Are you all right?
What's wrong?

656
00:56:53,946 --> 00:56:56,249
I felt a great disturbance in the Force...

657
00:56:56,349 --> 00:56:59,652
as if millions of voices
suddenly cried out in terror...

658
00:56:59,752 --> 00:57:01,684
and were suddenly silenced.

659
00:57:02,163 --> 00:57:04,205
I fear something terrible has happened.

660
00:57:06,091 --> 00:57:08,691
You'd better get on with your exercises.

661
00:57:11,038 --> 00:57:13,539
Well, you can forget your troubles
with those Imperial slugs.

662
00:57:13,564 --> 00:57:15,764
I told you I'd outrun them.

663
00:57:19,231 --> 00:57:21,324
Don't everybody thank me at once.

664
00:57:22,033 --> 00:57:25,927
Anyway, we should be at Alderaan
about 0200 hours.

665
00:57:33,352 --> 00:57:35,183
Now be careful, R2.

666
00:57:44,797 --> 00:57:47,297
He made a fair move.
Screaming about it can't help you.

667
00:57:47,565 --> 00:57:49,769
Let him have it.
It's not wise to upset a Wookiee.

668
00:57:49,928 --> 00:57:52,128
But, sir, nobody worries
about upsetting a droid.

669
00:57:52,438 --> 00:57:55,617
That's 'cause a droid don't pull
people's arms out of their sockets

670
00:57:55,642 --> 00:57:56,915
when they lose.

671
00:57:57,221 --> 00:57:58,868
Wookiees are known to do that.

672
00:58:01,405 --> 00:58:03,097
I see your point, sir.

673
00:58:03,122 --> 00:58:06,224
I suggest a new strategy, R2.
Let the Wookiee win.

674
00:58:25,003 --> 00:58:28,435
Remember, a Jedi can feel the Force
flowing through him.

675
00:58:29,234 --> 00:58:30,949
You mean it controls your actions?

676
00:58:30,973 --> 00:58:33,237
Partially, but it also obeys your commands.

677
00:58:39,016 --> 00:58:41,195
Hokey religions and
ancient weapons are no match

678
00:58:41,220 --> 00:58:42,949
for a good blaster at your side, kid.

679
00:58:43,961 --> 00:58:45,980
You don't believe in the Force, do you?

680
00:58:46,410 --> 00:58:48,907
Kid, I've flown from one side
of this galaxy to the other.

681
00:58:48,932 --> 00:58:52,079
I've seen a lot of strange stuff,
but I've never seen anything

682
00:58:52,104 --> 00:58:56,610
to make me believe there's one
all-powerful force controlling everything.

683
00:58:57,069 --> 00:59:00,327
There's no mystical
energy field controls my destiny.

684
00:59:00,931 --> 00:59:03,738
It's all a lot of simple tricks
and nonsense.

685
00:59:03,926 --> 00:59:06,643
I suggest you try it again, Luke.

686
00:59:08,139 --> 00:59:10,874
This time, let go your conscious self...

687
00:59:12,918 --> 00:59:14,879
and act on instinct.

688
00:59:16,162 --> 00:59:18,459
With the blast shield down,
I can't even see.

689
00:59:18,484 --> 00:59:19,831
How am I supposed to fight?

690
00:59:19,856 --> 00:59:22,656
Your eyes can deceive you.
Don't trust them.

691
00:59:31,737 --> 00:59:33,837
Stretch out with your feelings.

692
00:59:48,487 --> 00:59:50,935
You see? You can do it.

693
00:59:50,959 --> 00:59:52,117
I call it luck.

694
00:59:52,291 --> 00:59:54,853
In my experience,
there's no such thing as luck.

695
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:57,522
Look, good against remotes is one thing.

696
00:59:57,546 --> 01:00:00,304
Good against the living,
that's something else.

697
01:00:01,763 --> 01:00:03,947
Looks like we're coming up on Alderaan.

698
01:00:06,806 --> 01:00:09,608
You know, I did feel something.
I could almost see the remote.

699
01:00:09,708 --> 01:00:10,812
That's good.

700
01:00:10,998 --> 01:00:14,242
You've taken your first step
into a larger world.

701
01:00:19,277 --> 01:00:20,044
Yes?

702
01:00:21,136 --> 01:00:22,648
Our scout ships have reached Dantooine.

703
01:00:22,930 --> 01:00:24,800
They found the remains of a rebel base,

704
01:00:24,825 --> 01:00:27,194
but they estimate that it has been
deserted for some time.

705
01:00:27,453 --> 01:00:30,854
They are now conducting an extensive
search of the surrounding systems.

706
01:00:31,875 --> 01:00:34,259
She lied. She lied to us!

707
01:00:34,525 --> 01:00:38,302
I told you she would never
consciously betray the rebellion.

708
01:00:39,518 --> 01:00:41,552
Terminate her... immediately.

709
01:00:44,497 --> 01:00:47,397
Stand by, Chewie. Here we go.
Cut in the sublight engines.

710
01:00:50,115 --> 01:00:51,715
What the...?

711
01:00:54,559 --> 01:00:56,579
We've come out of hyperspace
into a meteor shower.

712
01:00:56,604 --> 01:00:59,487
Some kind of asteroid collision.
It's not on any of the charts.

713
01:00:59,547 --> 01:01:00,302
What's going on?

714
01:01:00,326 --> 01:01:02,825
Our position's correct,
except no Alderaan.

715
01:01:03,055 --> 01:01:04,273
What do you mean? Where is it?

716
01:01:04,298 --> 01:01:05,283
That's what I'm trying to tell you, kid.

717
01:01:05,308 --> 01:01:07,043
It ain't there.
It's been totally blown away.

718
01:01:07,125 --> 01:01:08,210
What? How?

719
01:01:08,240 --> 01:01:09,835
Destroyed by the Empire.

720
01:01:09,969 --> 01:01:12,058
The entire starfleet couldn't
destroy the whole planet.

721
01:01:12,083 --> 01:01:14,102
It would take a thousand ships
with more firepower than I've—

722
01:01:16,254 --> 01:01:17,551
There's another ship coming in.

723
01:01:17,576 --> 01:01:18,649
Maybe they know what happened.

724
01:01:18,673 --> 01:01:20,600
It's an Imperial fighter.

725
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:23,255
It followed us!

726
01:01:23,279 --> 01:01:24,892
No, it's a short-range fighter.

727
01:01:25,029 --> 01:01:28,029
There aren't any bases around here.
Where did it come from?

728
01:01:30,155 --> 01:01:32,900
It sure is leaving in a big hurry.
If they identify us, we're in big trouble.

729
01:01:32,950 --> 01:01:35,129
Not if I can help it.
Chewie, jam its transmissions.

730
01:01:35,226 --> 01:01:37,328
It would be as well to let it go.
It's too far out of range.

731
01:01:37,428 --> 01:01:39,228
Not for long.

732
01:01:42,500 --> 01:01:45,698
A fighter that size couldn't get
this deep into space on its own.

733
01:01:45,971 --> 01:01:48,507
He must have gotten lost,
been part of a convoy or something.

734
01:01:48,607 --> 01:01:51,402
Well, he ain't gonna be around
long enough to tell anybody about us.

735
01:01:53,879 --> 01:01:55,447
Look at him.
He's heading for that small moon.

736
01:01:55,547 --> 01:01:57,228
I think I can get him
before he gets there.

737
01:01:57,252 --> 01:01:58,448
He's almost in range.

738
01:01:59,984 --> 01:02:02,020
That's no moon.

739
01:02:02,140 --> 01:02:03,727
It's a space station.

740
01:02:03,764 --> 01:02:05,553
It's too big to be a space station.

741
01:02:08,861 --> 01:02:11,296
I have a very bad feeling about this.

742
01:02:11,396 --> 01:02:13,004
Turn the ship around.

743
01:02:13,218 --> 01:02:15,159
Yeah. I think you're right.

744
01:02:15,183 --> 01:02:17,715
Full reverse! Chewie, lock in
the auxiliary power.

745
01:02:22,507 --> 01:02:24,475
Chewie, lock in the auxiliary power!

746
01:02:26,845 --> 01:02:28,580
Why are we still moving towards it?!

747
01:02:28,665 --> 01:02:30,482
We're caught in a tractor beam.
It's pulling us in!

748
01:02:30,582 --> 01:02:31,943
– There's got to be
something you can do!

749
01:02:31,968 --> 01:02:33,345
There's nothing I can do about it, kid.

750
01:02:33,370 --> 01:02:35,247
I'm full power.
I'm gonna have to shut down.

751
01:02:35,271 --> 01:02:37,370
They're not gonna get me
without a fight.

752
01:02:41,226 --> 01:02:44,789
You can't win, but there are
alternatives to fighting.

753
01:03:01,373 --> 01:03:03,509
<i>Clear Bay 327.</i>

754
01:03:03,649 --> 01:03:06,049
<i>We're opening the magnetic field.</i>

755
01:03:20,599 --> 01:03:23,265
To your stations!
Come with me.

756
01:03:27,166 --> 01:03:30,791
<i>Close all outboard shields.
Close all outboard shields.</i>

757
01:03:32,577 --> 01:03:33,318
Yes?

758
01:03:33,342 --> 01:03:36,440
<i>We've captured a freighter entering
the remains of the Alderaan system.</i>

759
01:03:36,540 --> 01:03:40,423
<i>Its markings match those of a ship
that blasted its way out of Mos Eisley.</i>

760
01:03:40,626 --> 01:03:44,163
They must be trying to return
the stolen plans to the princess.

761
01:03:44,369 --> 01:03:47,338
She may yet be of some use to us.

762
01:03:52,364 --> 01:03:56,057
<i>Unlock 1, 5, 7, and 9.</i>
<i>Release charge.</i>

763
01:03:57,903 --> 01:04:00,030
<i>316, report to control.</i>

764
01:04:03,675 --> 01:04:05,095
There's no one on board, sir.

765
01:04:05,120 --> 01:04:07,836
According to the log, the crew
abandoned ship right after takeoff.

766
01:04:08,665 --> 01:04:11,437
It must be a decoy, sir. Several of the
escape pods have been jettisoned.

767
01:04:11,550 --> 01:04:12,862
Did you find any droids?

768
01:04:12,886 --> 01:04:13,573
No, sir.

769
01:04:13,598 --> 01:04:15,433
If there were any on board,
they must also have jettisoned.

770
01:04:15,520 --> 01:04:18,957
Send a scanning crew aboard.
I want every part of this ship checked.

771
01:04:19,057 --> 01:04:20,458
Yes, sir.

772
01:04:20,558 --> 01:04:24,652
I sense something...
a presence I've not felt since...

773
01:04:27,158 --> 01:04:28,833
Get me a scanning crew in here
on the double.

774
01:04:28,864 --> 01:04:31,265
I want every part of this ship checked.

775
01:04:50,530 --> 01:04:52,466
Boy, it's lucky you had these compartments.

776
01:04:52,708 --> 01:04:55,690
I use them for smuggling.
I never thought I'd be smuggling myself in 'em.

777
01:04:55,961 --> 01:04:57,248
This is ridiculous.

778
01:04:57,272 --> 01:04:59,981
Even if I could take off,
I'd never get past the tractor beam.

779
01:05:00,005 --> 01:05:01,393
Leave that to me.

780
01:05:01,552 --> 01:05:04,422
Damn fool, I knew that you
were gonna say that.

781
01:05:04,536 --> 01:05:07,996
Who's the more foolish, the fool
or the fool who follows him?

782
01:05:17,548 --> 01:05:18,669
The ship's all yours.

783
01:05:18,693 --> 01:05:22,186
If the scanners pick up anything,
report it immediately.

784
01:05:22,881 --> 01:05:24,581
All right, let's go.

785
01:05:39,097 --> 01:05:40,704
Hey, down there!

786
01:05:42,841 --> 01:05:44,484
Could you give us a hand with this?

787
01:05:53,384 --> 01:05:55,678
TK-421, why aren't you at your post?

788
01:05:56,588 --> 01:05:58,391
TK-421, do you copy?

789
01:06:11,102 --> 01:06:12,430
Take over. We've got a bad transmitter.

790
01:06:12,454 --> 01:06:14,502
I'll see what I can do.

791
01:06:31,522 --> 01:06:33,759
You know, between his howling
and your blasting everything in sight,

792
01:06:33,784 --> 01:06:35,994
it's a wonder the whole station
doesn't know we're here.

793
01:06:36,071 --> 01:06:39,405
Bring 'em on! I'd prefer a straight fight
to all this sneakin' around.

794
01:06:39,539 --> 01:06:41,275
We've found the computer outlet, sir.

795
01:06:41,300 --> 01:06:44,398
Plug in. He should be able to interpret
the entire Imperial network.

796
01:06:55,579 --> 01:06:59,125
He says he's found the main controls to the
power beam that's holding the ship here.

797
01:06:59,224 --> 01:07:01,819
He'll try to make the precise location
appear on the monitor.

798
01:07:12,262 --> 01:07:13,802
I don't think you boys can help.

799
01:07:14,395 --> 01:07:15,509
I must go alone.

800
01:07:15,534 --> 01:07:16,709
Whatever you say.

801
01:07:16,733 --> 01:07:19,004
I've done more than I bargained
for on this trip already.

802
01:07:19,104 --> 01:07:20,372
I want to go with you.

803
01:07:20,439 --> 01:07:22,742
Be patient, Luke.
Stay and watch over the droids.

804
01:07:22,875 --> 01:07:23,688
But he can—

805
01:07:23,713 --> 01:07:24,640
They must be delivered safely,

806
01:07:24,664 --> 01:07:28,181
or other star systems will suffer
the same fate as Alderaan.

807
01:07:28,383 --> 01:07:31,975
Your destiny lies along
a different path from mine.

808
01:07:35,600 --> 01:07:38,934
The Force will be with you...
always.

809
01:07:48,329 --> 01:07:50,590
You said it, Chewie.

810
01:07:50,614 --> 01:07:53,255
Where did you dig up that old fossil?

811
01:07:54,300 --> 01:07:55,903
Ben is a great man.

812
01:07:55,928 --> 01:07:57,433
Yeah, great at getting us into trouble.

813
01:07:57,457 --> 01:07:58,932
I didn't hear you give any ideas.

814
01:07:59,087 --> 01:08:01,752
Well, anything's better than just hangin' around
waiting for 'em to pick us up.

815
01:08:01,777 --> 01:08:03,677
Who do you think—

816
01:08:04,371 --> 01:08:05,230
What is it?

817
01:08:05,871 --> 01:08:07,660
I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir.

818
01:08:07,736 --> 01:08:10,505
He says “I've found her”
and keeps repeating “She's here.”

819
01:08:10,604 --> 01:08:13,054
Well, who... who has he found?

820
01:08:13,247 --> 01:08:14,216
Princess Leia.

821
01:08:14,454 --> 01:08:15,797
The princess? She's here?!

822
01:08:15,822 --> 01:08:16,586
Princess?!

823
01:08:16,610 --> 01:08:17,550
Where? Where is she?

824
01:08:17,575 --> 01:08:19,575
Princess?! What's going on?

825
01:08:25,038 --> 01:08:28,290
Level 5, Detention Block AA-23.

826
01:08:32,719 --> 01:08:35,139
I'm afraid she's scheduled
to be terminated.

827
01:08:35,843 --> 01:08:38,346
Oh, no! We've got to do something!

828
01:08:38,520 --> 01:08:39,756
What are you talking about?

829
01:08:39,780 --> 01:08:40,947
The droids belong to her.

830
01:08:40,972 --> 01:08:42,808
She's the one in the message.
We gotta help her.

831
01:08:42,958 --> 01:08:44,510
Now look, don't get any funny ideas.

832
01:08:44,534 --> 01:08:46,062
The old man wants us to wait right here.

833
01:08:46,087 --> 01:08:47,370
But he didn't know she was here.

834
01:08:47,394 --> 01:08:49,246
Just find a way back
into that detention block.

835
01:08:49,431 --> 01:08:50,881
I'm not going anywhere.

836
01:08:50,905 --> 01:08:52,069
They're going to execute her.

837
01:08:52,094 --> 01:08:54,471
Look, a few minutes ago, you said you didn't
want to just wait here to be captured.

838
01:08:54,496 --> 01:08:55,814
Now, all you want to do is stay?

839
01:08:55,839 --> 01:08:58,560
Marching into the detention area
is not what I had in mind.

840
01:08:58,585 --> 01:08:59,881
But they're gonna kill her!

841
01:08:59,905 --> 01:09:01,712
Better her than me!

842
01:09:09,597 --> 01:09:10,763
She's rich.

843
01:09:13,815 --> 01:09:14,424
Rich?

844
01:09:14,448 --> 01:09:16,384
Mm-hmm. Rich, powerful.

845
01:09:16,437 --> 01:09:19,507
Listen, if you were to rescue her,
the reward would be...

846
01:09:19,654 --> 01:09:20,520
What?

847
01:09:20,544 --> 01:09:22,590
Well, more wealth than
you can imagine.

848
01:09:22,690 --> 01:09:24,445
I don't know, I can imagine quite a bit.

849
01:09:24,469 --> 01:09:25,691
You'll get it.

850
01:09:25,791 --> 01:09:26,459
I better.

851
01:09:26,483 --> 01:09:27,371
You will.

852
01:09:28,500 --> 01:09:29,474
All right, kid.

853
01:09:29,498 --> 01:09:30,598
You better be right about this.

854
01:09:30,698 --> 01:09:31,355
All right.

855
01:09:31,380 --> 01:09:32,500
What's your plan?

856
01:09:32,525 --> 01:09:33,581
Uh...

857
01:09:33,723 --> 01:09:35,868
3PO, hand me those
binders there, will you?

858
01:09:37,798 --> 01:09:38,920
Okay...

859
01:09:39,760 --> 01:09:41,990
Now... I'm gonna put these on you.

860
01:09:43,341 --> 01:09:46,127
Okay Han, you... you put those on.

861
01:09:47,308 --> 01:09:49,968
Don't worry, Chewie.
I think I know what he has in mind.

862
01:09:50,651 --> 01:09:52,778
Master Luke, sir,
pardon me for asking, but

863
01:09:52,854 --> 01:09:55,734
What should R2 and I do
if we're discovered here?

864
01:09:56,090 --> 01:09:57,303
Lock the door.

865
01:09:57,327 --> 01:09:59,533
And hope they don't have blasters.

866
01:09:59,558 --> 01:10:01,558
That isn't very reassuring.

867
01:10:21,935 --> 01:10:25,935
<i>517 to scanner control.
517 to scanner control.</i>

868
01:10:30,258 --> 01:10:32,458
<i>316, report to control.</i>

869
01:10:35,930 --> 01:10:39,930
<i>53 to upper bay door.
53 to upper bay door.</i>

870
01:10:53,021 --> 01:10:54,907
I can't see a thing in this helmet.

871
01:11:26,713 --> 01:11:28,021
This is not gonna work.

872
01:11:28,045 --> 01:11:29,373
Why didn't you say so before?

873
01:11:29,477 --> 01:11:31,768
I did say so before.

874
01:11:46,613 --> 01:11:49,354
Where are you taking this... thing?

875
01:11:49,704 --> 01:11:52,079
Prisoner transfer from Cell Block 1138.

876
01:11:53,846 --> 01:11:55,218
I wasn't notified.

877
01:11:55,946 --> 01:11:57,151
I'll have to clear it.

878
01:12:04,204 --> 01:12:05,059
Look out! He's loose!

879
01:12:05,083 --> 01:12:06,373
He'll tear us all apart!

880
01:12:06,687 --> 01:12:08,287
I'll get him!

881
01:12:31,186 --> 01:12:32,272
Look out!

882
01:12:42,283 --> 01:12:44,752
We've got to find out which cell
this princess of yours is in.

883
01:12:44,777 --> 01:12:48,873
Here it is... 2187. You go and get her.
I'll hold them here.

884
01:12:52,999 --> 01:12:55,727
Uh, everything's under control.
Situation normal.

885
01:12:55,751 --> 01:12:56,504
<i>What happened?</i>

886
01:12:56,529 --> 01:12:59,002
Uh, had a slight weapons malfunction,

887
01:12:59,026 --> 01:13:01,601
but, uh, everything's
perfectly all right now.

888
01:13:01,626 --> 01:13:04,829
We're fine... We're all fine
here now. Thank you.

889
01:13:04,853 --> 01:13:06,097
How are you?

890
01:13:06,153 --> 01:13:07,464
<i>We're sending a squad up.</i>

891
01:13:07,595 --> 01:13:09,279
Uh, negative, negative!

892
01:13:09,303 --> 01:13:11,904
We have a... a reactor
leak here, uh, now.

893
01:13:12,079 --> 01:13:13,404
Give us a few minutes to lock it down.

894
01:13:13,428 --> 01:13:15,590
Uh, large leak, very dangerous.

895
01:13:15,690 --> 01:13:17,881
<i>Who is this? What's your</i>
<i>operating number?</i>

896
01:13:18,133 --> 01:13:19,633
Uh...

897
01:13:20,941 --> 01:13:22,346
Boring conversation anyway.

898
01:13:22,370 --> 01:13:25,110
Luke! We're gonna have company!

899
01:13:38,412 --> 01:13:40,715
Aren't you a little short for a stormtrooper?

900
01:13:40,740 --> 01:13:43,533
Huh?
Oh, the uniform.

901
01:13:45,005 --> 01:13:46,951
I'm Luke Skywalker.
I'm here to rescue you.

902
01:13:47,265 --> 01:13:48,106
You're who?

903
01:13:48,130 --> 01:13:49,201
I'm here to rescue you.

904
01:13:49,226 --> 01:13:50,943
I've got your R2 unit.
I'm here with Ben Kenobi.

905
01:13:50,968 --> 01:13:51,965
Ben Kenobi?! Where is he?

906
01:13:51,989 --> 01:13:52,981
Come on!

907
01:13:55,241 --> 01:13:56,702
He is here.

908
01:13:56,974 --> 01:13:58,395
Obi-Wan Kenobi?

909
01:13:59,186 --> 01:14:00,481
What makes you think so?

910
01:14:00,707 --> 01:14:02,375
A tremor in the Force.

911
01:14:02,523 --> 01:14:06,526
The last time I felt it was
in the presence of my old master.

912
01:14:06,787 --> 01:14:09,049
Surely he must be dead by now.

913
01:14:09,543 --> 01:14:12,058
Don't underestimate the Force.

914
01:14:12,567 --> 01:14:14,095
The Jedi are extinct.

915
01:14:14,119 --> 01:14:16,384
Their fire has gone out
of the universe.

916
01:14:16,580 --> 01:14:19,773
You, my friend, are all that's left
of their religion.

917
01:14:20,042 --> 01:14:20,959
Yes.

918
01:14:21,193 --> 01:14:24,793
<i>We have an emergency alert
in Detention Block AA-23.</i>

919
01:14:25,633 --> 01:14:28,202
The princess?
Put all sections on alert.

920
01:14:28,348 --> 01:14:31,712
Obi-Wan is here.
The Force is with him.

921
01:14:31,851 --> 01:14:34,664
If you're right, he must not be
allowed to escape.

922
01:14:34,842 --> 01:14:36,579
Escape is not his plan.

923
01:14:36,603 --> 01:14:38,672
I must face him alone.

924
01:14:47,894 --> 01:14:49,694
Get behind me!
Get behind me!

925
01:15:01,001 --> 01:15:03,760
Watch your left.
They went down the cell bay.

926
01:15:06,167 --> 01:15:07,320
Can't get out that way.

927
01:15:07,345 --> 01:15:09,046
Looks like you managed to cut off
our only escape route.

928
01:15:09,342 --> 01:15:12,542
Maybe you'd like it back in your cell,
Your Highness.

929
01:15:14,208 --> 01:15:16,644
– C-3PO, C-3PO!
– <i>Yes, sir?</i>

930
01:15:16,690 --> 01:15:18,249
Are there any other ways
out of the cell bay?

931
01:15:18,273 --> 01:15:19,761
We've been cut off!

932
01:15:22,649 --> 01:15:24,776
What was that? I didn't copy.

933
01:15:24,884 --> 01:15:28,220
I said all systems have been alerted
to your presence, sir.

934
01:15:28,288 --> 01:15:30,637
The main entrance seems
to be the only way in or out.

935
01:15:30,810 --> 01:15:33,114
All other information
on your level is restricted.

936
01:15:33,180 --> 01:15:35,580
Open up in there! Open up in there!

937
01:15:37,100 --> 01:15:38,243
Oh, no!

938
01:15:38,626 --> 01:15:40,726
There isn't any other way out!

939
01:15:45,747 --> 01:15:47,927
I can't hold them off forever!
Now what?!

940
01:15:47,976 --> 01:15:49,495
This is some rescue!

941
01:15:49,666 --> 01:15:51,547
You came in here, and you didn't
have a plan for getting out?

942
01:15:51,572 --> 01:15:53,880
He's the brains, sweetheart!

943
01:15:53,904 --> 01:15:55,217
Well, I didn't...

944
01:15:56,784 --> 01:15:58,090
What the hell are you doing?

945
01:15:58,114 --> 01:16:00,221
Somebody has to save our skins.

946
01:16:02,310 --> 01:16:04,443
Into the garbage chute, flyboy.

947
01:16:11,632 --> 01:16:13,432
Get in there!

948
01:16:13,893 --> 01:16:17,223
Get in there, you big furry oaf!
I don't care what you smell.

949
01:16:17,925 --> 01:16:20,292
Get in there, and don't worry about it.

950
01:16:22,843 --> 01:16:24,943
Wonderful girl!

951
01:16:25,946 --> 01:16:28,714
Either I'm going to kill her,
or I'm beginning to like her.

952
01:16:30,852 --> 01:16:32,752
Get in there!

953
01:16:45,259 --> 01:16:48,089
The garbage chute was
a really wonderful idea.

954
01:16:48,854 --> 01:16:51,749
What an incredible smell
you've discovered!

955
01:16:54,442 --> 01:16:56,053
Let's get out of here.

956
01:16:56,078 --> 01:16:57,453
Get away from there.

957
01:16:58,185 --> 01:16:59,086
No, wait!

958
01:17:05,086 --> 01:17:07,905
Will you forget it? I already tried it!
It's magnetically sealed.

959
01:17:07,930 --> 01:17:10,399
Put that thing away!
You're gonna get us all killed!

960
01:17:10,510 --> 01:17:12,007
Absolutely, Your Worship.

961
01:17:12,032 --> 01:17:14,878
Look, I had everything under control
till you led us down here!

962
01:17:15,196 --> 01:17:17,596
You know, it's not gonna take 'em long
to figure out what happened to us!

963
01:17:17,657 --> 01:17:19,657
It could be worse.

964
01:17:23,957 --> 01:17:25,079
It's worse.

965
01:17:25,103 --> 01:17:26,649
There's something alive in here.

966
01:17:26,674 --> 01:17:28,904
That's your imagination.

967
01:17:28,929 --> 01:17:30,888
Something just moved past my leg.

968
01:17:32,606 --> 01:17:34,606
Look! Did you see that?

969
01:17:34,962 --> 01:17:35,990
What?

970
01:17:57,370 --> 01:17:59,104
Kid! Luke!

971
01:18:02,863 --> 01:18:03,777
Luke!

972
01:18:11,423 --> 01:18:13,486
Luke, grab hold of this!

973
01:18:13,861 --> 01:18:15,963
Blast it, will you?
My gun's jammed.

974
01:18:15,996 --> 01:18:16,844
Where?

975
01:18:17,197 --> 01:18:18,431
Anywhere!

976
01:18:26,667 --> 01:18:28,267
Luke, Luke!

977
01:18:51,392 --> 01:18:53,698
Help him!
What happened?

978
01:18:54,008 --> 01:18:57,941
I don't know. It just let go of me
and disappeared.

979
01:19:03,884 --> 01:19:06,211
I've got a bad feeling about this.

980
01:19:12,000 --> 01:19:13,065
The walls are moving!

981
01:19:13,090 --> 01:19:15,825
Don't just stand there!
Try and brace it with something.

982
01:19:23,931 --> 01:19:24,871
Help me!

983
01:19:38,511 --> 01:19:39,725
Wait a minute!

984
01:19:42,676 --> 01:19:45,549
3PO!
Come in, 3PO!

985
01:19:46,694 --> 01:19:49,348
<i>3PO!
Where could he be?</i>

986
01:19:54,473 --> 01:19:56,753
Take over. See to him.

987
01:19:59,588 --> 01:20:01,057
Look, there.

988
01:20:02,896 --> 01:20:03,981
They're madmen!

989
01:20:04,013 --> 01:20:05,350
They're heading for the prison level.

990
01:20:05,374 --> 01:20:06,928
If you hurry, you might catch them.

991
01:20:07,380 --> 01:20:08,415
Follow me.

992
01:20:12,640 --> 01:20:14,100
You stand guard.

993
01:20:19,339 --> 01:20:20,572
Come on.

994
01:20:24,451 --> 01:20:25,651
Oh!

995
01:20:28,582 --> 01:20:31,818
All this excitement has overrun
the circuits in my counterpart here.

996
01:20:31,944 --> 01:20:35,011
If you don't mind, I'd like to take him
down to maintenance.

997
01:20:35,146 --> 01:20:36,073
All right.

998
01:20:48,910 --> 01:20:51,763
3PO!
Come in, 3PO!

999
01:20:51,788 --> 01:20:53,223
3PO!

1000
01:20:53,314 --> 01:20:54,778
Get on top!

1001
01:20:55,023 --> 01:20:55,752
I can't!

1002
01:20:55,777 --> 01:21:01,074
Where could he be?! 3PO!
3PO, will you come in!

1003
01:21:01,755 --> 01:21:03,752
They aren't here. Something
must have happened to them.

1004
01:21:04,149 --> 01:21:06,842
See if they've been captured.
Hurry!

1005
01:21:10,611 --> 01:21:13,446
One thing's for sure.
We're all gonna be a lot thinner.

1006
01:21:16,016 --> 01:21:16,951
Get on top of it.

1007
01:21:16,975 --> 01:21:18,481
I'm trying.

1008
01:21:24,144 --> 01:21:27,337
Thank goodness they haven't found them!
Where could they be?

1009
01:21:29,563 --> 01:21:30,918
Use the comlink?

1010
01:21:31,185 --> 01:21:33,945
Oh, my. I forgot.
I turned it off.

1011
01:21:37,990 --> 01:21:39,427
Are you there, sir?

1012
01:21:39,493 --> 01:21:40,576
3PO?!

1013
01:21:41,095 --> 01:21:42,338
We've had some problems.

1014
01:21:42,362 --> 01:21:43,897
<i>Will you shut up and listen to me?!</i>

1015
01:21:43,922 --> 01:21:46,825
Shut down all the garbage mashers
on the detention level, will ya?!

1016
01:21:46,850 --> 01:21:47,678
Do you copy!?

1017
01:21:47,702 --> 01:21:49,850
Shut down all the garbage mashers
on the detention level!

1018
01:21:51,878 --> 01:21:54,448
<i>Shut down all the garbage mashers
on the detention level!</i>

1019
01:21:54,555 --> 01:21:57,055
No! Shut them all down.
Hurry!

1020
01:22:08,875 --> 01:22:09,921
What?

1021
01:22:13,599 --> 01:22:15,903
Listen to them.
They're dying, R2!

1022
01:22:15,928 --> 01:22:20,935
Curse my metal body! I wasn't fast enough.
It's all my fault! My poor master.

1023
01:22:21,288 --> 01:22:24,553
We're all right!
<i>You did great!</i>

1024
01:22:24,577 --> 01:22:28,081
Hey, open the pressure maintenance hatch
on unit number... where are we?

1025
01:22:28,106 --> 01:22:30,886
 <i>3263827!</i>

1026
01:23:16,889 --> 01:23:20,581
If we can just avoid any more female advice,
we ought to be able to get outta here.

1027
01:23:20,634 --> 01:23:22,588
Well, let's get moving.

1028
01:23:24,104 --> 01:23:25,838
Where are you going?

1029
01:23:26,266 --> 01:23:28,634
No, wait! They'll hear!

1030
01:23:30,037 --> 01:23:32,380
Come here, you big coward.
Chewie, come here.

1031
01:23:32,405 --> 01:23:33,806
Listen...

1032
01:23:34,099 --> 01:23:36,963
I don't know who you are
or where you came from.

1033
01:23:37,103 --> 01:23:40,046
But from now on, you do
as I tell you, okay?

1034
01:23:40,660 --> 01:23:43,598
Look, Your Worshipfulness,
let's get one thing straight.

1035
01:23:43,623 --> 01:23:46,759
I take orders from just one person... me!

1036
01:23:46,853 --> 01:23:48,512
It's a wonder you're still alive.

1037
01:23:48,889 --> 01:23:52,059
Will somebody get this big
walking carpet out of my way?

1038
01:23:52,233 --> 01:23:54,733
No reward is worth this!

1039
01:24:04,805 --> 01:24:06,733
Give me regular reports, please.

1040
01:24:06,757 --> 01:24:07,911
Right.

1041
01:24:10,310 --> 01:24:11,551
Do you know what's going on?

1042
01:24:11,575 --> 01:24:13,310
Maybe it's another drill.

1043
01:24:18,451 --> 01:24:20,354
You seen that new VT-16?

1044
01:24:20,454 --> 01:24:22,623
Yeah. Some of the other guys
were telling me about it.

1045
01:24:22,723 --> 01:24:24,625
They say it's... it's quite a thing to see.

1046
01:24:24,725 --> 01:24:26,214
What was that?

1047
01:24:27,120 --> 01:24:29,778
Ah, it's nothing. Outgassing.
Don't worry about it.

1048
01:24:35,335 --> 01:24:36,263
There she is.

1049
01:24:36,287 --> 01:24:37,738
C-3PO? Do you copy?

1050
01:24:37,913 --> 01:24:38,693
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1051
01:24:38,718 --> 01:24:39,575
Are you safe?

1052
01:24:39,599 --> 01:24:40,901
<i>For the moment.</i>

1053
01:24:41,001 --> 01:24:43,340
We're in the main hangar
across from the ship.

1054
01:24:45,245 --> 01:24:47,039
We're right above you. Stand by.

1055
01:24:47,063 --> 01:24:48,448
You came in that thing?!

1056
01:24:48,528 --> 01:24:49,685
You're braver than I thought!

1057
01:24:49,709 --> 01:24:51,227
Nice! Come on.

1058
01:24:55,302 --> 01:24:56,997
It's them!
Blast them!

1059
01:24:58,525 --> 01:25:01,094
– Get back to the ship!
– Where are you going? Come back!

1060
01:25:01,145 --> 01:25:01,943
He certainly has courage.

1061
01:25:01,967 --> 01:25:04,020
What good will it do us 
if he gets himself killed?

1062
01:25:04,045 --> 01:25:05,545
Come on.

1063
01:25:30,336 --> 01:25:32,190
I think we took a wrong turn.

1064
01:25:37,698 --> 01:25:39,064
There's no lock!

1065
01:25:42,674 --> 01:25:44,009
That oughta hold them for a while.

1066
01:25:44,033 --> 01:25:45,552
Quick! We've got to get across.

1067
01:25:45,577 --> 01:25:47,508
Find the controls that extend the bridge.

1068
01:25:47,532 --> 01:25:48,847
I think I just blasted it.

1069
01:25:48,995 --> 01:25:50,694
They're coming through!

1070
01:26:12,893 --> 01:26:14,226
Here, hold this.

1071
01:26:31,097 --> 01:26:32,724
Here they come.

1072
01:26:43,422 --> 01:26:44,402
For luck.

1073
01:26:50,969 --> 01:26:55,969
We think they may be splitting up.
They may be on Level 5 and 6 now, sir.

1074
01:27:09,882 --> 01:27:11,882
Where could they be?

1075
01:27:24,679 --> 01:27:26,981
Open the blast doors!
Open the blast doors!

1076
01:27:45,525 --> 01:27:48,109
I've been waiting for you, Obi-Wan.

1077
01:27:48,133 --> 01:27:49,885
We meet again at last.

1078
01:27:50,996 --> 01:27:53,100
The circle is now complete.

1079
01:27:53,166 --> 01:27:55,207
When I left you,
I was but the learner.

1080
01:27:55,231 --> 01:27:57,637
Now I am the master.

1081
01:27:57,697 --> 01:28:00,397
Only a master of evil, Darth.

1082
01:28:19,793 --> 01:28:22,562
Your powers are weak, old man.

1083
01:28:22,662 --> 01:28:24,556
You can't win, Darth.

1084
01:28:24,655 --> 01:28:26,126
If you strike me down,

1085
01:28:26,151 --> 01:28:29,552
I shall become more powerful
than you can possibly imagine.

1086
01:28:36,915 --> 01:28:39,213
You should not have come back.

1087
01:29:04,738 --> 01:29:07,668
Didn't we just leave this party?

1088
01:29:09,088 --> 01:29:09,990
What kept you?

1089
01:29:10,014 --> 01:29:11,491
We, uh, ran into some old friends.

1090
01:29:11,531 --> 01:29:12,318
The ship all right?

1091
01:29:12,348 --> 01:29:14,039
It seems okay, if we can get to it.

1092
01:29:14,094 --> 01:29:16,894
I just hope the old man got
the tractor beam out of commission.

1093
01:29:31,264 --> 01:29:32,230
Look!

1094
01:29:35,542 --> 01:29:37,467
Come on, R2, we're going.

1095
01:29:39,072 --> 01:29:40,247
Now's our chance! Go!

1096
01:29:44,003 --> 01:29:44,957
Ben?

1097
01:30:00,507 --> 01:30:02,007
No!

1098
01:30:10,504 --> 01:30:13,504
– Come on!
– Come on! Come on!

1099
01:30:13,968 --> 01:30:15,725
Luke, it's too late!

1100
01:30:15,749 --> 01:30:17,468
Blast the door, kid!

1101
01:30:26,593 --> 01:30:28,326
<i>Run, Luke, run!</i>

1102
01:30:32,058 --> 01:30:34,071
I hope that old man got that
tractor beam out of commission,

1103
01:30:34,096 --> 01:30:37,224
or this is gonna be a real short trip.
Okay, hit it!

1104
01:31:08,394 --> 01:31:10,967
We're coming up on their sentry ships.
Hold them off.

1105
01:31:10,992 --> 01:31:13,792
Angle the deflector shields
while I charge up the main guns.

1106
01:31:22,943 --> 01:31:24,469
I can't believe he's gone.

1107
01:31:28,994 --> 01:31:30,894
There wasn't anything
you could have done.

1108
01:31:31,270 --> 01:31:33,739
Come on, buddy.
We're not out of this yet.

1109
01:31:50,329 --> 01:31:53,089
You in, kid?
Okay, stay sharp.

1110
01:32:03,470 --> 01:32:05,270
Here they come.

1111
01:32:22,600 --> 01:32:24,600
They're coming in too fast!

1112
01:32:32,479 --> 01:32:34,060
We've lost the lateral controls!

1113
01:32:34,085 --> 01:32:36,637
Don't worry. She'll hold together.

1114
01:32:37,957 --> 01:32:39,957
Hear me, baby? Hold together.

1115
01:33:01,975 --> 01:33:03,783
Got him! I got him!

1116
01:33:03,807 --> 01:33:05,908
Great, kid! Don't get cocky.

1117
01:33:07,414 --> 01:33:09,377
There's still two more of them out there!

1118
01:33:42,883 --> 01:33:44,198
That's it! We did it!

1119
01:33:44,222 --> 01:33:45,803
We did it!

1120
01:33:46,526 --> 01:33:49,386
Help! I think I'm melting!
This is all your fault!

1121
01:33:57,130 --> 01:33:58,543
Are they away?

1122
01:33:58,752 --> 01:34:01,463
They've just made the jump
into hyperspace.

1123
01:34:01,822 --> 01:34:05,324
You're sure the homing beacon
is secure aboard their ship?

1124
01:34:06,397 --> 01:34:08,482
I'm taking an awful risk, Vader.

1125
01:34:09,022 --> 01:34:10,939
This had better work.

1126
01:34:11,472 --> 01:34:13,680
Not a bad bit of rescuing, huh?

1127
01:34:13,780 --> 01:34:16,585
You know, sometimes
I amaze even myself.

1128
01:34:17,237 --> 01:34:19,057
That doesn't sound too hard.

1129
01:34:19,492 --> 01:34:20,766
They let us go.

1130
01:34:20,790 --> 01:34:23,204
It's the only explanation
for the ease of our escape.

1131
01:34:23,392 --> 01:34:24,904
Easy? You call that easy?

1132
01:34:24,928 --> 01:34:26,051
They're tracking us.

1133
01:34:26,259 --> 01:34:27,959
Not this ship, sister.

1134
01:34:29,174 --> 01:34:31,777
At least the information
in R2 is still intact.

1135
01:34:31,851 --> 01:34:34,232
What's so important?
What's he carrying?

1136
01:34:34,256 --> 01:34:36,722
The technical readouts
of that battle station.

1137
01:34:37,577 --> 01:34:40,390
I only hope that when the data's analyzed,
a weakness can be found.

1138
01:34:40,954 --> 01:34:42,315
It's not over yet.

1139
01:34:42,459 --> 01:34:44,146
It is for me, sister.

1140
01:34:44,317 --> 01:34:47,747
Look, I ain't in this for your revolution,
and I'm not in it for you, Princess.

1141
01:34:47,848 --> 01:34:50,544
I expect to be well paid.
I'm in it for the money.

1142
01:34:50,850 --> 01:34:52,753
You needn't worry about your reward.

1143
01:34:52,853 --> 01:34:56,253
If money is all that you love,
then that's what you'll receive.

1144
01:34:59,159 --> 01:35:01,020
Your friend is quite a mercenary.

1145
01:35:01,044 --> 01:35:03,177
I wonder if he really cares
about anything...

1146
01:35:03,202 --> 01:35:04,571
...or anybody.

1147
01:35:05,504 --> 01:35:06,304
I care!

1148
01:35:13,679 --> 01:35:14,753
So...

1149
01:35:15,719 --> 01:35:17,393
What do you think of her, Han?

1150
01:35:17,518 --> 01:35:19,317
I'm trying not to, kid.

1151
01:35:20,339 --> 01:35:21,339
Good.

1152
01:35:25,084 --> 01:35:27,704
Still, she's got a lot of spirit.

1153
01:35:29,795 --> 01:35:31,162
I don't know.
What do you think?

1154
01:35:31,186 --> 01:35:32,874
You think a princess
and a guy like me—

1155
01:35:32,899 --> 01:35:33,879
No.

1156
01:36:21,174 --> 01:36:22,056
You're safe.

1157
01:36:22,080 --> 01:36:24,377
When we heard about Alderaan,
we feared the worst.

1158
01:36:24,490 --> 01:36:26,455
We have no time for
sorrows, Commander.

1159
01:36:26,479 --> 01:36:29,502
You must use the information in this
R2 unit to help plan the attack.

1160
01:36:29,526 --> 01:36:31,077
It's our only hope.

1161
01:36:52,679 --> 01:36:53,260
Yes.

1162
01:36:53,284 --> 01:36:55,199
<i>We're approaching the planet Yavin.</i>

1163
01:36:55,393 --> 01:36:57,812
<i>The rebel base is on a moon
on the far side.</i>

1164
01:36:57,891 --> 01:37:00,322
<i>We are preparing to orbit the planet.</i>

1165
01:37:08,755 --> 01:37:11,069
The battle station is heavily shielded,

1166
01:37:11,093 --> 01:37:14,515
and carries a firepower
greater than half the starfleet.

1167
01:37:15,248 --> 01:37:19,478
Its defenses are designed around
a direct large-scale assault.

1168
01:37:19,799 --> 01:37:24,899
A small, one-man fighter should be able
to penetrate the outer defense.

1169
01:37:26,424 --> 01:37:30,163
Pardon me for asking, sir, but what good are
snub fighters going to be against that?

1170
01:37:30,269 --> 01:37:34,777
Well, the Empire doesn't consider a small,
one-man fighter to be any threat,

1171
01:37:34,801 --> 01:37:37,347
or they'd have a
tighter defense.

1172
01:37:37,730 --> 01:37:40,956
An analysis of the plans
provided by Princess Leia

1173
01:37:40,981 --> 01:37:44,286
has demonstrated a weakness
in the battle station.

1174
01:37:44,744 --> 01:37:47,180
The approach will not be easy.

1175
01:37:47,527 --> 01:37:50,452
You're required to maneuver
straight down this trench,

1176
01:37:50,477 --> 01:37:53,277
and skim the surface to this point.

1177
01:37:53,967 --> 01:37:56,753
The target area is only two meters wide.

1178
01:37:56,890 --> 01:38:00,854
It's a small thermal exhaust port
right below the main port.

1179
01:38:01,833 --> 01:38:04,838
The shaft leads directly
to the reactor system.

1180
01:38:04,910 --> 01:38:09,773
A precise hit will start a chain reaction,
which should destroy the station.

1181
01:38:10,003 --> 01:38:13,193
Only a precise hit will
set up a chain reaction.

1182
01:38:13,640 --> 01:38:16,810
The shaft is ray-shielded,
so you'll have to use proton torpedoes.

1183
01:38:17,290 --> 01:38:19,092
That's impossible, even for a computer.

1184
01:38:19,116 --> 01:38:20,272
It's not impossible.

1185
01:38:20,297 --> 01:38:22,930
I used to bull's-eye womp rats
in my T-16 back home.

1186
01:38:22,955 --> 01:38:24,667
They're not much bigger than two meters.

1187
01:38:25,564 --> 01:38:28,913
Then man your ships,
and may the Force be with you.

1188
01:38:36,983 --> 01:38:39,774
<i>Orbiting the planet at maximum velocity.</i>

1189
01:38:40,165 --> 01:38:43,574
<i>The moon with the rebel base
will be in range in 30 minutes.</i>

1190
01:38:44,161 --> 01:38:46,724
This will be a day
long remembered.

1191
01:38:46,748 --> 01:38:48,823
It has seen the end of Kenobi,

1192
01:38:48,847 --> 01:38:51,414
and will soon see the
end of the rebellion.

1193
01:38:57,130 --> 01:39:00,130
<i>All flight crews, man your stations.</i>

1194
01:39:00,693 --> 01:39:03,693
<i>All flight crews, man your stations.</i>

1195
01:39:06,205 --> 01:39:09,051
So... you got your reward
and you're just leaving, then?

1196
01:39:09,076 --> 01:39:10,876
That's right. Yeah.

1197
01:39:12,050 --> 01:39:14,259
I've got some old debts
I've got to pay off with this stuff.

1198
01:39:14,840 --> 01:39:18,940
And even if I didn't, you don't think I'd be
fool enough to stick around here, do you?

1199
01:39:19,418 --> 01:39:20,634
Why don't you come with us?

1200
01:39:20,658 --> 01:39:22,879
You're pretty good in a fight.
We could use you.

1201
01:39:22,988 --> 01:39:25,706
Come on. Why don't you
take a look around?

1202
01:39:25,858 --> 01:39:28,194
You know what's about to happen,
what they're up against.

1203
01:39:28,488 --> 01:39:31,691
They could use a good pilot like you.
You're turning your back on them.

1204
01:39:31,864 --> 01:39:34,267
What good's a reward
if you ain't around to use it?

1205
01:39:34,325 --> 01:39:37,095
Besides, attacking that battle station
ain't my idea of courage.

1206
01:39:37,237 --> 01:39:39,786
It's more like... suicide.

1207
01:39:41,593 --> 01:39:44,497
All right.
Well, take care of yourself, Han.

1208
01:39:44,670 --> 01:39:46,622
I guess that's what you're best at, isn't it?

1209
01:39:47,652 --> 01:39:48,995
Hey, Luke.

1210
01:39:52,111 --> 01:39:53,838
May the Force be with you.

1211
01:40:00,981 --> 01:40:04,412
What are you looking at?
I know what I'm doing.

1212
01:40:08,611 --> 01:40:13,611
<i>All pilots to your stations.
All pilots to your stations.</i>

1213
01:40:19,688 --> 01:40:20,663
What's wrong?

1214
01:40:20,687 --> 01:40:21,773
Oh, it's Han.

1215
01:40:22,089 --> 01:40:24,370
I don't know. I really thought
he'd change his mind.

1216
01:40:24,954 --> 01:40:27,990
He's got to follow his own path.
No one can choose it for him.

1217
01:40:29,464 --> 01:40:31,664
I only wish Ben were here.

1218
01:40:39,709 --> 01:40:41,842
<i>Open main launch tubes.</i>

1219
01:40:43,913 --> 01:40:46,780
<i>Main launch tubes opening, sir.</i>

1220
01:40:51,821 --> 01:40:55,157
Hey, this R2 unit of yours seems a bit
beat up. You want a new one?

1221
01:40:55,332 --> 01:40:56,108
Not on your life.

1222
01:40:56,132 --> 01:40:58,073
That little droid and I have
been through a lot together.

1223
01:40:58,227 --> 01:41:00,127
You okay, R2?

1224
01:41:00,896 --> 01:41:01,973
Good.

1225
01:41:03,232 --> 01:41:06,232
<i>Gold squadron, begin takeoff procedure.</i>

1226
01:41:06,562 --> 01:41:09,226
Hang on tight, R2.
You've got to come back.

1227
01:41:11,388 --> 01:41:13,612
You wouldn't want my life
to get boring, would you?

1228
01:42:02,291 --> 01:42:06,291
<i>Luke, the Force will be with you.</i>

1229
01:42:16,972 --> 01:42:19,972
<i>Standby alert.
Death Star approaching.</i>

1230
01:42:20,435 --> 01:42:23,635
<i>Estimated time to firing range, 15 minutes.</i>

1231
01:42:36,692 --> 01:42:37,828
All wings report in.

1232
01:42:37,864 --> 01:42:38,928
Red 10 standing by.

1233
01:42:38,953 --> 01:42:40,153
<i>Red Seven standing by.</i>

1234
01:42:40,181 --> 01:42:41,239
Red Three standing by.

1235
01:42:41,268 --> 01:42:42,648
Red Six standing by.

1236
01:42:42,672 --> 01:42:44,067
Red Nine standing by.

1237
01:42:44,100 --> 01:42:45,136
Red Two standing by.

1238
01:42:45,165 --> 01:42:46,469
<i>Red 11 standing by.</i>

1239
01:42:46,569 --> 01:42:48,038
Red Five standing by.

1240
01:42:49,705 --> 01:42:52,305
Lock S-foils in attack position.

1241
01:42:55,678 --> 01:42:57,899
<i>We're passing through their magnetic field.</i>

1242
01:42:57,923 --> 01:42:58,948
Hold tight.

1243
01:42:59,008 --> 01:43:02,673
<i>Switch your deflectors on.
Double front.</i>

1244
01:43:05,120 --> 01:43:06,700
Look at the size of that thing!

1245
01:43:06,740 --> 01:43:08,097
<i>Cut the chatter, Red Two.</i>

1246
01:43:08,122 --> 01:43:10,217
Accelerate to attack speed.

1247
01:43:12,995 --> 01:43:14,250
This is it, boys.

1248
01:43:14,274 --> 01:43:15,732
Red Leader, this is Gold Leader.

1249
01:43:15,757 --> 01:43:16,988
I copy, Gold Leader.

1250
01:43:17,012 --> 01:43:18,761
We're starting for the target shaft now.

1251
01:43:18,818 --> 01:43:19,736
We're in position.

1252
01:43:19,760 --> 01:43:22,714
I'm going to cut across the axis
and try and draw their fire.

1253
01:43:36,772 --> 01:43:38,467
<i>Heavy fire, boss, 23 degrees.</i>

1254
01:43:38,491 --> 01:43:40,172
<i>I see it. Stay low.</i>

1255
01:43:47,441 --> 01:43:49,741
This is Red Five. I'm going in.

1256
01:43:53,508 --> 01:43:55,408
<i>Luke, pull up!</i>

1257
01:43:56,405 --> 01:43:57,266
Are you all right?

1258
01:43:57,290 --> 01:43:59,137
I got a little cooked,
but I'm okay.

1259
01:44:04,579 --> 01:44:06,348
We count 30 rebel ships, Lord Vader.

1260
01:44:06,409 --> 01:44:08,411
But they're so small,
they're evading our turbolasers.

1261
01:44:08,656 --> 01:44:10,601
We'll have to destroy
them ship to ship.

1262
01:44:10,625 --> 01:44:12,479
Get the crews to their fighters.

1263
01:44:15,156 --> 01:44:16,172
Watch yourself.

1264
01:44:16,197 --> 01:44:19,717
There's a lot of fire coming from the
right side of that deflection tower.

1265
01:44:19,795 --> 01:44:20,572
I'm on it.

1266
01:44:20,596 --> 01:44:22,532
I'm going in.
Cover me, Porkins.

1267
01:44:22,632 --> 01:44:24,932
I'm right with you, Red Three.

1268
01:44:30,206 --> 01:44:32,006
I've got a problem here.

1269
01:44:32,031 --> 01:44:32,727
Eject!

1270
01:44:32,752 --> 01:44:33,580
I can hold it.

1271
01:44:33,634 --> 01:44:34,294
Pull up!

1272
01:44:34,318 --> 01:44:36,034
No, no, I'm all—

1273
01:44:40,069 --> 01:44:43,069
<i>The rebel base will be in firing range
in seven minutes.</i>

1274
01:44:46,882 --> 01:44:50,082
<i>Luke, trust your feelings.</i>

1275
01:44:57,733 --> 01:45:01,570
Squad leaders, we've
picked up a new group of signals.

1276
01:45:01,657 --> 01:45:03,210
Enemy fighters coming your way.

1277
01:45:03,403 --> 01:45:05,103
My scope's negative.
I don't see anything.

1278
01:45:05,128 --> 01:45:06,491
Pick up your visual scanning.

1279
01:45:06,515 --> 01:45:07,736
<i>Here they come.</i>

1280
01:45:10,500 --> 01:45:12,800
Watch it. You've got one on your tail.

1281
01:45:17,466 --> 01:45:18,486
I'm hit!

1282
01:45:19,988 --> 01:45:21,457
You've picked one up! Watch it!

1283
01:45:21,482 --> 01:45:23,088
I can't see it!

1284
01:45:24,459 --> 01:45:26,759
He's on me tight.
I can't shake him!

1285
01:45:28,122 --> 01:45:30,022
I'll be right there.

1286
01:45:42,210 --> 01:45:44,696
Several fighters have broken off
from the main group.

1287
01:45:44,721 --> 01:45:46,069
Come with me.

1288
01:45:49,051 --> 01:45:51,132
<i>Pull in! Luke, pull in!</i>

1289
01:45:51,157 --> 01:45:52,001
Watch your back, Luke.

1290
01:45:52,025 --> 01:45:54,957
<i>Watch your back.
Fighters above you, coming in.</i>

1291
01:46:00,850 --> 01:46:03,552
I'm hit, but not bad.
R2, see what you can do with it.

1292
01:46:03,623 --> 01:46:05,823
Hang on back there.

1293
01:46:06,435 --> 01:46:08,600
<i>Red Six, can you see Red Five?</i>

1294
01:46:08,730 --> 01:46:11,499
<i>There's a heavy fire zone...
Red Five, where are you?</i>

1295
01:46:11,524 --> 01:46:13,224
I can't shake him!

1296
01:46:16,519 --> 01:46:18,488
I'm on him, Luke. Hold on.

1297
01:46:21,323 --> 01:46:23,450
Blast it, Biggs! Where are you?

1298
01:46:30,285 --> 01:46:31,287
Thanks, Wedge.

1299
01:46:31,311 --> 01:46:32,721
<i>Good shooting, Wedge.</i>

1300
01:46:32,942 --> 01:46:36,403
Red Leader, this is Gold Leader.
We're starting our attack run.

1301
01:46:37,752 --> 01:46:40,566
<i>I copy, Gold Leader.
Move into position.</i>

1302
01:46:42,770 --> 01:46:45,076
Stay in attack formation.

1303
01:46:45,167 --> 01:46:48,268
The exhaust port is marked and locked in.

1304
01:46:53,802 --> 01:46:56,925
<i>Switch all power to
front deflector screens.</i>

1305
01:46:57,038 --> 01:47:00,312
<i>Switch all power to
front deflector screens.</i>

1306
01:47:04,753 --> 01:47:06,749
How many guns do you think, Gold Five?

1307
01:47:06,929 --> 01:47:09,965
<i>Say about 20 guns. Some on the surface,
some on the towers.</i>

1308
01:47:10,018 --> 01:47:12,723
<i>Death Star will be
in range in five minutes.</i>

1309
01:47:15,143 --> 01:47:17,343
Switch to targeting computer.

1310
01:47:20,434 --> 01:47:22,893
Computer locked.
Getting a signal.

1311
01:47:25,147 --> 01:47:27,638
The guns!
They've stopped!

1312
01:47:28,800 --> 01:47:31,501
Stabilize your rear deflectors.
Watch for enemy fighters.

1313
01:47:31,601 --> 01:47:34,418
They're coming in!
Three marks at 210.

1314
01:47:36,091 --> 01:47:38,097
I'll take them myself. Cover me.

1315
01:47:38,190 --> 01:47:39,257
Yes, sir.

1316
01:47:53,755 --> 01:47:55,337
It's no good. I can't maneuver.

1317
01:47:55,362 --> 01:47:56,392
Stay on target.

1318
01:47:56,458 --> 01:47:57,324
We're too close.

1319
01:47:57,348 --> 01:47:58,851
Stay on target.

1320
01:48:00,362 --> 01:48:01,842
Loosen up!

1321
01:48:04,220 --> 01:48:07,089
Gold Five to Red Leader,
lost Tiree, lost Hutch.

1322
01:48:07,175 --> 01:48:08,142
I copy, Gold Leader.

1323
01:48:08,166 --> 01:48:09,932
They came from behind.

1324
01:48:15,800 --> 01:48:18,526
We've analyzed their attack, sir,
and there is a danger.

1325
01:48:18,626 --> 01:48:20,330
Should I have your ship standing by?

1326
01:48:20,670 --> 01:48:23,445
Evacuate?
In our moment of triumph?

1327
01:48:23,469 --> 01:48:26,070
I think you overestimate
their chances.

1328
01:48:26,608 --> 01:48:29,101
<i>Rebel base, three minutes and closing.</i>

1329
01:48:29,690 --> 01:48:31,280
Red boys, this is Red Leader.

1330
01:48:31,304 --> 01:48:33,294
<i>Rendezvous at mark 6.1.</i>

1331
01:48:33,415 --> 01:48:34,868
<i>This is Red Two flying toward you.</i>

1332
01:48:34,892 --> 01:48:36,561
<i>Red Three standing by.</i>

1333
01:48:37,066 --> 01:48:38,767
Red Leader, this is Base One.

1334
01:48:38,987 --> 01:48:41,353
<i>Keep half your group out of range
for the next run.</i>

1335
01:48:41,444 --> 01:48:44,177
<i>Copy, Base One.
Luke, take Red Two and Three.</i>

1336
01:48:44,286 --> 01:48:47,277
Hold up here and wait for
my signal to start your run.

1337
01:48:56,404 --> 01:48:57,664
This is it!

1338
01:49:01,833 --> 01:49:03,933
We should be able to see it by now.

1339
01:49:05,500 --> 01:49:07,978
Keep your eyes open for those fighters.

1340
01:49:09,151 --> 01:49:10,213
There's too much interference.

1341
01:49:10,237 --> 01:49:11,687
Red Five, can you see them
from where you are?

1342
01:49:11,854 --> 01:49:14,193
No sign of any... Wait.
<i>Coming in .35.</i>

1343
01:49:14,218 --> 01:49:15,278
I see them.

1344
01:49:16,292 --> 01:49:17,680
I'm in range.

1345
01:49:18,661 --> 01:49:20,293
Target's coming up.

1346
01:49:22,964 --> 01:49:25,298
Just hold them off for a few seconds.

1347
01:49:25,938 --> 01:49:27,766
Close up formation.

1348
01:49:29,344 --> 01:49:31,539
Almost there.

1349
01:49:39,993 --> 01:49:41,708
You'd better let her loose.
They're right behind me.

1350
01:49:41,732 --> 01:49:43,513
Almost there.

1351
01:49:44,653 --> 01:49:46,553
I can't hold them.

1352
01:49:54,366 --> 01:49:56,066
It's away!

1353
01:49:59,712 --> 01:50:00,674
<i>It's a hit!</i>

1354
01:50:00,698 --> 01:50:01,554
<i>Negative.</i>

1355
01:50:01,579 --> 01:50:02,754
Negative.

1356
01:50:02,778 --> 01:50:03,906
It didn't go in.

1357
01:50:03,931 --> 01:50:06,893
<i>It just impacted on the surface.</i>

1358
01:50:12,741 --> 01:50:14,015
<i>Red Leader, we're right above you.</i>

1359
01:50:14,052 --> 01:50:17,046
Turn to .05.
We'll cover for you.

1360
01:50:17,093 --> 01:50:20,393
Stay there.
I just lost my starboard engine.

1361
01:50:20,921 --> 01:50:23,385
Get set up for your attack run.

1362
01:50:36,238 --> 01:50:38,724
<i>Rebel base, one minute and closing.</i>

1363
01:50:39,584 --> 01:50:42,992
<i>Biggs, Wedge, let's close it up.
We're going in full throttle.</i>

1364
01:50:43,017 --> 01:50:44,821
That ought to keep those
fighters off our back.

1365
01:50:44,845 --> 01:50:46,721
Right with you, boss.

1366
01:50:46,949 --> 01:50:49,451
Luke, at that speed, will you be able
to pull out in time?

1367
01:50:49,551 --> 01:50:51,876
It'll be just like Beggar's Canyon
back home.

1368
01:50:58,613 --> 01:51:00,633
We'll stay back far enough to cover you.

1369
01:51:00,658 --> 01:51:03,454
<i>My scope shows the tower,
but I can't see the exhaust port.</i>

1370
01:51:03,699 --> 01:51:05,907
Are you sure the computer can hit it?

1371
01:51:08,537 --> 01:51:10,741
Watch yourself.
Increase speed, full throttle.

1372
01:51:10,765 --> 01:51:12,139
What about that tower?

1373
01:51:12,239 --> 01:51:15,070
You worry about those fighters!
I'll worry about the tower!

1374
01:51:20,949 --> 01:51:24,800
R2, that stabilizer's broken loose again.
See if you can't lock it down.

1375
01:51:33,862 --> 01:51:35,992
Fighters coming in .3.

1376
01:51:44,405 --> 01:51:45,133
<i>I'm hit!</i>

1377
01:51:45,157 --> 01:51:46,048
I can't stay with you!

1378
01:51:46,073 --> 01:51:48,308
Get clear, Wedge.
You can't do any more good back there.

1379
01:51:48,457 --> 01:51:50,057
Sorry.

1380
01:51:50,612 --> 01:51:52,846
Let him go.
Stay on the leader.

1381
01:51:55,284 --> 01:51:58,284
Hurry, Luke. They're coming in much faster
this time. We can't hold them.

1382
01:52:01,800 --> 01:52:03,900
R2, try and increase the power.

1383
01:52:09,898 --> 01:52:12,698
<i>Hurry up, Luke!
Wait! Quick!</i>

1384
01:52:20,049 --> 01:52:22,940
<i>Rebel base, 30 seconds and closing.</i>

1385
01:52:23,111 --> 01:52:25,011
I'm on the leader.

1386
01:52:27,636 --> 01:52:29,335
Hang on, R2.

1387
01:52:44,899 --> 01:52:46,807
<i>Use the Force, Luke.</i>

1388
01:52:50,124 --> 01:52:51,602
<i>Let go, Luke.</i>

1389
01:52:53,842 --> 01:52:55,996
The Force is strong with this one.

1390
01:52:56,238 --> 01:52:57,860
<i>Luke, trust me.</i>

1391
01:53:03,344 --> 01:53:04,745
<i>His computer's off.</i>

1392
01:53:04,770 --> 01:53:06,624
<i>Luke, you switched off
your targeting computer! </i>

1393
01:53:06,648 --> 01:53:07,341
<i>What's wrong?</i>

1394
01:53:07,543 --> 01:53:09,543
<i>Nothing. I'm all right.</i>

1395
01:53:23,184 --> 01:53:24,784
<i>I've lost R2!</i>

1396
01:53:26,114 --> 01:53:28,114
<i>The Death Star has cleared the planet.</i>

1397
01:53:28,310 --> 01:53:30,310
<i>The Death Star has cleared the planet.</i>

1398
01:53:31,513 --> 01:53:33,393
<i>Rebel base in range.</i>

1399
01:53:33,632 --> 01:53:35,513
You may fire when ready.

1400
01:53:36,051 --> 01:53:38,051
<i>Commence primary ignition.</i>

1401
01:53:51,520 --> 01:53:53,381
I have you now.

1402
01:53:55,300 --> 01:53:56,260
What?

1403
01:53:56,392 --> 01:53:57,433
Yahoo!

1404
01:53:59,241 --> 01:54:00,750
Look out!

1405
01:54:06,815 --> 01:54:10,148
You're all clear, kid!
Now let's blow this thing and go home!

1406
01:54:16,658 --> 01:54:18,258
<i>Stand by.</i>

1407
01:54:21,429 --> 01:54:23,029
<i>Stand by.</i>

1408
01:54:32,934 --> 01:54:35,334
Great shot, kid!
That was one in a million!

1409
01:54:36,357 --> 01:54:40,557
<i>Remember, the Force</i>
<i>will be with you always.</i>

1410
01:55:00,034 --> 01:55:01,534
Luke!

1411
01:55:04,686 --> 01:55:06,087
Hey! Hey!

1412
01:55:06,234 --> 01:55:07,903
I knew you'd come back.
I just knew it.

1413
01:55:07,928 --> 01:55:10,254
Well, I wasn't going to let you get
all the credit and take all the reward.

1414
01:55:10,279 --> 01:55:13,096
Hey, I knew there was more
to you than money.

1415
01:55:13,534 --> 01:55:14,589
Oh, no!

1416
01:55:14,613 --> 01:55:17,134
Oh, my. R2, can you hear me?

1417
01:55:17,879 --> 01:55:19,059
Say something.

1418
01:55:19,271 --> 01:55:20,799
You can repair him, can't you?

1419
01:55:20,875 --> 01:55:22,741
We'll get to work on him right away.

1420
01:55:22,765 --> 01:55:24,245
You must repair him.

1421
01:55:24,270 --> 01:55:27,228
Sir, if any of my circuits or gears will help,
I'll gladly donate them.

1422
01:55:27,301 --> 01:55:29,401
He'll be all right.

